1
00:00:04,750 --> 00:00:08,208
.. [ Piano: ''The Entertainer'' ]

2
00:00:44,957 --> 00:00:48,893
.. [ Band Playing ''The Entertainer'' ]

3
00:02:34,866 --> 00:02:37,835
- [ All Chattering, lndistinct ]
- Let's see what you got.

4
00:02:37,903 --> 00:02:42,169
- l need more runners. l can't
write the business fast enough.
- You gotta see Granger.

5
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:45,835
[ Chattering Continues ]

6
00:02:49,181 --> 00:02:53,311
8720. Yeah. Yeah.
Hold it a minute.

7
00:02:53,385 --> 00:02:57,321
Beat it, Mottola ! Mr. Granger ?
Chicago's on the line.

8
00:02:59,124 --> 00:03:01,058
Yeah.

9
00:03:01,126 --> 00:03:04,220
This is Combs. Why haven't we
heard from you ? Everybody else is in.

10
00:03:04,296 --> 00:03:06,890
We had problems
with the law this morning.

11
00:03:06,965 --> 00:03:09,456
The mayor promised
to get tough on the rackets,

12
00:03:09,534 --> 00:03:12,469
so l shut everybody down for
a couple of hours to make it look good.

13
00:03:12,537 --> 00:03:15,563
- Nothing serious. lt just
put us a little behind.
- Been making your payoffs ?

14
00:03:15,640 --> 00:03:18,803
Hell, yes ! He does this every year.
There's nothing to worry about.

15
00:03:18,877 --> 00:03:23,246
Finish your count and get it up here.
l don't want to be here all night.

16
00:03:23,315 --> 00:03:25,408
The man's going
to be real happy.

17
00:03:25,484 --> 00:03:28,578
- Looks like we cleared
over ten grand this week.
- We cleared 22 here.

18
00:03:28,653 --> 00:03:31,781
What the hell !
You got the whole Chicago South Side.

19
00:03:31,857 --> 00:03:34,519
How do you expect the eight lousy spots
l got to compete with that ?

20
00:03:34,593 --> 00:03:38,529
They did 14 grand in Evanston,
16.5 in Gary, and 20 in Cicero.

21
00:03:38,597 --> 00:03:41,191
Looks like you're
bringing up the rear.

22
00:03:41,266 --> 00:03:44,167
l just got the count.
l'll put the take on the 4:15.

23
00:03:44,236 --> 00:03:46,329
We'll be waiting.

24
00:03:49,007 --> 00:03:51,441
Mottola !

25
00:03:52,577 --> 00:03:56,240
Take this up to Chicago
on the 4:15.

26
00:03:56,314 --> 00:03:59,579
They'll be waiting for it
at the clearinghouse.

27
00:03:59,651 --> 00:04:04,418
And don't stop for any entertainment.
Get a cab over on 7th.

28
00:04:04,489 --> 00:04:07,014
- Aw, cut it out !
- [ Phone Ringing ]

29
00:04:07,092 --> 00:04:09,026
8720.

30
00:04:16,601 --> 00:04:19,570
[ Car Horn Honks ]

31
00:04:21,807 --> 00:04:25,140
Hey, you there ! Stop !
Hey, you ! Stop that man !

32
00:04:25,210 --> 00:04:29,146
Stop him ! He's got my wallet !
Stop him ! Stop that man !

33
00:04:29,214 --> 00:04:31,478
He's got all of my money !

34
00:04:31,550 --> 00:04:33,575
Stop him !
Stop him !

35
00:04:34,786 --> 00:04:37,482
Goddamn nigger-lover !

36
00:04:40,192 --> 00:04:42,854
l'm gonna get you someday for this !
Sucker egg !

37
00:04:42,928 --> 00:04:47,058
Don't let him get away ! He's got
my wallet ! He's got all my money !

38
00:04:47,132 --> 00:04:50,067
- My wallet ! He's got my wallet !
- We got it !

39
00:04:50,135 --> 00:04:53,229
- What happened ?
Did he get you with the knife ?
- Give it to me, please.

40
00:04:53,305 --> 00:04:56,240
- You need a doctor. l'll call a cop.
- No, no ! No cops !

41
00:04:58,510 --> 00:05:01,001
You wanted by the law
or something ?

42
00:05:01,079 --> 00:05:04,207
No, it's okay.

43
00:05:04,282 --> 00:05:07,615
Are you nuts, carrying a wad like that
in a neighborhood like this ?

44
00:05:07,686 --> 00:05:11,850
Thanks. l'm obliged to you.
l gotta get going. [ Groans ]

45
00:05:11,923 --> 00:05:14,357
You ain't going nowhere
on this leg.

46
00:05:14,426 --> 00:05:18,362
l gotta. Gotta run some slots
in West Bend for a mob here.

47
00:05:18,430 --> 00:05:22,560
l got a little behind in the payoffs.
They think l've been holding out on 'em.

48
00:05:22,634 --> 00:05:25,694
They gave me 'til 4:00
to come up with the cash.

49
00:05:25,770 --> 00:05:29,763
- lf they don't get it, l'm dead.
- lt don't look good, Gramps.
lt's almost 4:00 now.

50
00:05:29,841 --> 00:05:33,709
l'll give you and your friend
a hundred bucks to deliver it for me.

51
00:05:35,447 --> 00:05:38,939
l don't know. That mug that hit you
is mad enough at me already.

52
00:05:39,017 --> 00:05:41,645
What if he's around the corner,
waiting with some friends ?

53
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:44,314
He won't know you're carrying it.
You've gotta help me.

54
00:05:44,389 --> 00:05:47,825
l'm sorry, pal. l'm gonna
maybe help you get to a doctor,

55
00:05:47,893 --> 00:05:50,088
but l ain't about to walk
into no knife for you.

56
00:05:50,161 --> 00:05:52,629
How about you ? All you gotta do
is put it in the door slot.

57
00:05:52,697 --> 00:05:54,631
l'll give you the whole 100.

58
00:05:54,699 --> 00:05:58,396
- What makes you think you can
trust him ? He didn't do shit.
- Butt out, chicken liver !

59
00:05:58,470 --> 00:06:00,904
l gave him back the wallet.
How far is this place ?

60
00:06:00,972 --> 00:06:05,341
1811 Mason. Put it in box 3-C.
You won't have no trouble.

61
00:06:06,811 --> 00:06:09,177
There's $5,000 there,

62
00:06:09,247 --> 00:06:11,681
and here's
a hundred bucks for you.

63
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:16,744
Okay, l'll make your drop for you.
And don't worry, you can trust me.

64
00:06:16,821 --> 00:06:19,688
Hey. Hey !

65
00:06:19,758 --> 00:06:22,454
lf those goons search you, you ain't
gonna get far carrying it there.

66
00:06:22,527 --> 00:06:25,462
- What'll we do ?
- You got a bag or something ?

67
00:06:25,530 --> 00:06:28,465
- How about a handkerchief ?
- Here's a handkerchief !

68
00:06:28,533 --> 00:06:31,127
Give it to me.
Give me the money.

69
00:06:31,202 --> 00:06:34,467
Just hurry, will you ?

70
00:06:34,539 --> 00:06:38,532
You got any more ? Better give it
all to me if you want to keep it.

71
00:06:38,610 --> 00:06:42,137
They think l've been holding out
on 'em. My wife got sick,
and l had to pay the bill.

72
00:06:42,213 --> 00:06:45,239
- l wasn't holding out on 'em.
- Stuff it down your pants here,
like that.

73
00:06:45,317 --> 00:06:47,285
- Got it ?
- Uh-huh.

74
00:06:47,352 --> 00:06:50,480
- Hurry, will ya ?
- Ain't a tough guy in the world
that's gonna frisk you there.

75
00:06:50,555 --> 00:06:52,887
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

76
00:06:57,429 --> 00:07:00,626
[ Car Horn Honking,
Trolley Bell Dinging ]

77
00:07:05,570 --> 00:07:07,663
- [ Engine Starting ]
- Where to ?

78
00:07:07,739 --> 00:07:10,264
- Which way is Mason ?
- Twenty blocks south.

79
00:07:10,342 --> 00:07:13,311
- Go north, Joliet Station, fast !
- Right.

80
00:07:14,813 --> 00:07:17,611
[ Laughing ]

81
00:07:17,682 --> 00:07:22,142
- What's so funny ?
- l just made the world's
easiest five grand !

82
00:07:22,220 --> 00:07:24,484
[ Chuckling ]

83
00:07:33,665 --> 00:07:36,532
- Come on, Luther ! Come on !
- Hold on, man ! Okay !

84
00:07:36,601 --> 00:07:39,536
- Hustle !
- [ Panting, Laughing ]

85
00:07:41,606 --> 00:07:44,131
ln here !

86
00:07:45,677 --> 00:07:48,942
[ Laughing ]
Man, was that beautiful !

87
00:07:49,014 --> 00:07:51,812
l thought for sure
he was on to us.

88
00:07:51,883 --> 00:07:54,784
l had him all the way.
[ Laughing ] All the way !

89
00:07:54,853 --> 00:07:59,017
[ Laughing ]
Ah !

90
00:07:59,090 --> 00:08:02,617
Wai-- Luther.

91
00:08:02,694 --> 00:08:04,958
Good God !
We're millionaires.

92
00:08:05,030 --> 00:08:07,464
- Jesus ! Did you know
he was that loaded ?
- Hell, no !

93
00:08:07,532 --> 00:08:11,468
l just cut into him. l would've
settled for pawning one of them shoes.

94
00:08:11,536 --> 00:08:14,096
- [ Both Laughing ]
- Oh, God !

95
00:08:14,172 --> 00:08:17,403
- Do you-- [ Laughing ]
- [ Laughing ]

96
00:08:17,475 --> 00:08:20,967
- Whoo !
- Come on. Let's get out of here.
We'll split it up tonight.

97
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:45,892
[ Heels Clacking ]

98
00:08:57,982 --> 00:09:00,416
Heya, Marge !

99
00:09:03,021 --> 00:09:07,185
.. [ Band Playing Striptease Tune ]

100
00:09:07,258 --> 00:09:10,591
[ Scattered Applause ]

101
00:09:10,662 --> 00:09:13,927
- Hi, kid.
- Hi, Hooker. She's on stage.

102
00:09:18,703 --> 00:09:21,137
Hi, Hooker.
Gettin' married or something ?

103
00:09:21,206 --> 00:09:24,801
Get used to it, Leonard.
l'm going to look this good from now on.

104
00:09:24,876 --> 00:09:27,276
- Whaddaya say, Ed ?
- Hi, Hooker.

105
00:09:27,345 --> 00:09:29,813
[ Man Whistling ]

106
00:09:39,791 --> 00:09:42,885
- [ Whistles ] Hey ! Psst !
- [ Man Whistles ]

107
00:09:42,961 --> 00:09:45,225
l wanna talk--

108
00:09:48,266 --> 00:09:51,064
[ Scattered Applause ]

109
00:09:51,136 --> 00:09:54,697
Hey, Hooker, you gettin'
married or somethin' ?

110
00:09:57,509 --> 00:10:00,103
[ Man Whistling ]

111
00:10:00,178 --> 00:10:02,976
For Christ's sake, Ed,
did you hear that ?

112
00:10:03,047 --> 00:10:05,572
Harry drops four beats
in the middle of my goddamn routine !

113
00:10:05,650 --> 00:10:08,915
- How long do l gotta put up with that ?
- Crystal ! Leonard, you're on.

114
00:10:08,987 --> 00:10:11,922
You wanna get outta here tonight ?
l come into some dough.

115
00:10:11,990 --> 00:10:15,482
l can't. l got a 10:00.
l need the five bucks.

116
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:17,960
l'll spend 50 on you.

117
00:10:18,029 --> 00:10:20,725
- Yeah ?
- Yeah.

118
00:10:20,798 --> 00:10:25,292
- Okay.
- ...opens up his pants,
the duck sticks his head out.

119
00:10:25,370 --> 00:10:28,305
One lady says to the other,
''See what l see ?''

120
00:10:28,373 --> 00:10:31,308
She says, ''So what ?
You've seen one, you've seen 'em all.''

121
00:10:31,376 --> 00:10:34,539
- She says, ''Yes, but this one's
eating my popcorn.''
- [ Men Laughing ]

122
00:10:34,612 --> 00:10:37,740
[ Patrons Chattering, Shouting ]

123
00:10:37,815 --> 00:10:41,376
You see that guy Harry,
he can't keep time.

124
00:10:41,452 --> 00:10:44,546
Supposing there's
some Hollywood movie agent out there.

125
00:10:44,622 --> 00:10:47,557
- All those years of training
right down the drain.
- Whaddaya say, Jimmy ?

126
00:10:47,625 --> 00:10:50,890
- Ain't seen you in months.
Thought you took a fall.
- Just a little hard times.

127
00:10:50,962 --> 00:10:53,954
- Everything's jake now.
- How about a ten spot on the line ?

128
00:10:54,032 --> 00:10:56,967
There's a lot of action there
on 28th Street. Pay you 35--

129
00:10:58,036 --> 00:10:59,867
Three grand on the red.

130
00:10:59,938 --> 00:11:02,099
- $3,000 ?
- Are you nuts ?

131
00:11:02,173 --> 00:11:06,303
- [ Hooker ] No, l feel lucky.
- Hooker, l can't accept that.
lt's too big a bet.

132
00:11:06,377 --> 00:11:08,937
- There's a house limit.
- Take it.

133
00:11:09,013 --> 00:11:11,072
- But Hooker here--
- Take it !

134
00:11:11,149 --> 00:11:13,674
[ Ball Rolling ]

135
00:11:18,856 --> 00:11:21,950
- [ Crowd Murmuring ]
- Twenty-two, black.

136
00:11:23,161 --> 00:11:25,721
Tough luck, kid.

137
00:11:25,797 --> 00:11:30,461
Lucky for me it came up black.
A fella could get in trouble here,
losin' a bet like that.

138
00:11:30,535 --> 00:11:33,800
Listen, Jimmy,
can't we do it again, huh ?

139
00:11:38,710 --> 00:11:41,770
[ Dealer ]
Seven !

140
00:11:43,348 --> 00:11:46,613
Don't worry about it. There's always
more where that came from.

141
00:11:46,684 --> 00:11:49,312
Oh, don't worry about it, he says.
Three thousand dollars !

142
00:11:49,387 --> 00:11:51,014
Thanks, Hooker.

143
00:11:51,089 --> 00:11:54,217
[ Crystal ] Comes in here with $50
he's going to spend on me !

144
00:11:54,292 --> 00:11:57,159
[ Patrons Shouting ]

145
00:11:57,228 --> 00:11:59,662
- Thanks for the evening, Hooker.
- lt's not over yet.

146
00:11:59,731 --> 00:12:03,167
- Next time you wanna
spend $50 on me, mail it.
- Come on, would you--

147
00:12:03,234 --> 00:12:05,828
Listen, will ya pl--

148
00:12:59,023 --> 00:13:03,084
They found Mottola, drunk in a dive
in Joliet. He never got on the train.

149
00:13:03,161 --> 00:13:06,221
l don't wanna hear about his day, Greer.
What happened to the money ?

150
00:13:06,297 --> 00:13:09,926
He lost it to a couple of con artists
on his way out of the spot.

151
00:13:10,001 --> 00:13:12,936
- How much ?
- Eleven thousand.

152
00:13:15,573 --> 00:13:18,940
Okay, l better get
on the phone to New York,

153
00:13:19,010 --> 00:13:22,673
see what the big mick
wants to do about it.

154
00:13:22,747 --> 00:13:25,181
l have a pretty good idea, though.

155
00:13:27,552 --> 00:13:30,851
[ lndistinct Chatter ]

156
00:13:30,922 --> 00:13:32,856
Oh !

157
00:13:38,696 --> 00:13:41,062
[ Man ]
Come on !

158
00:13:48,439 --> 00:13:50,669
[ Dealer ]
Ace. Bet the ace.

159
00:13:50,742 --> 00:13:53,506
- Bet the ace. Ace bets a deuce.
- Ace says two.

160
00:13:53,578 --> 00:13:56,012
- Two.
- [ Chips Clacking ]

161
00:13:56,080 --> 00:13:58,207
On his right.

162
00:13:58,282 --> 00:14:02,878
Four fives, two spades,
ace six, ace deuce.

163
00:14:04,222 --> 00:14:07,521
- Ten--
- Ace, l'll bet ace. Two again.

164
00:14:10,061 --> 00:14:13,121
- Doyle, can l talk to you ?
- l'm busy, Floyd.

165
00:14:13,197 --> 00:14:16,724
lt's important. We had
a little trouble in Chicago today.

166
00:14:16,801 --> 00:14:20,328
One of our runners
got hit for 11 grand.

167
00:14:20,405 --> 00:14:23,533
What makes you think
he just didn't pocket it ?

168
00:14:23,608 --> 00:14:28,102
We checked his story with a tipster.
He was cleaned by two grifters.

169
00:14:28,179 --> 00:14:33,947
- They working for anybody ?
- l don't know. Could be.
We're running that down now.

170
00:14:34,018 --> 00:14:37,715
Have some local people
take care of them. Nothing fancy.

171
00:14:37,789 --> 00:14:40,690
Got to discourage
this kind of thing.

172
00:14:42,460 --> 00:14:44,894
You follow ?

173
00:14:50,067 --> 00:14:53,332
[ Radio Show, lndistinct ]

174
00:14:53,404 --> 00:14:57,807
[ Radio: Machine Gun Fire ]

175
00:15:02,914 --> 00:15:05,474
- Johnny Hooker ! Aah !
- [ Radio Show Continues, lndistinct ]

176
00:15:05,550 --> 00:15:08,519
-lf you ain't a sharper in them linens !
-Evenin', Louise.

177
00:15:08,586 --> 00:15:12,920
- Hey, Ma !
- lf l didn't know you better,
l'd swear you had some class.

178
00:15:12,990 --> 00:15:16,926
- [ Laughing ]
- Johnny, Luther said you was
something to see today !

179
00:15:16,994 --> 00:15:19,019
Oh ! l don't know, Alva.

180
00:15:19,096 --> 00:15:22,827
l gotta get faster tyin' up
that bundle. l'm still giving
'em too much time to think.

181
00:15:22,900 --> 00:15:27,337
Bushwah ! l used to make that switch
with slower hands than you got.

182
00:15:27,405 --> 00:15:30,272
'Course, the Up and Down Broadway
was my best game.

183
00:15:30,341 --> 00:15:34,402
Me and Luther didn't make much on it,
but it wasn't so touchy.

184
00:15:34,479 --> 00:15:38,381
Them marks can beat you up bad
when they catch you makin' that switch.

185
00:15:38,449 --> 00:15:41,111
- Come on, Leroy.
We'll be late for church.
- Aw, Ma !

186
00:15:41,185 --> 00:15:45,121
- They were closin' in
on Machine Gun Kelly.
- Who you rootin' for anyhow ?

187
00:15:45,189 --> 00:15:48,124
- Hey, Hooker !
- Can't help you, Leroy.
You can't beat the house.

188
00:15:48,192 --> 00:15:50,990
- Nuts !
- Since when do you go
to church at night ?

189
00:15:51,062 --> 00:15:53,155
Since they started late bingo.

190
00:15:53,231 --> 00:15:56,166
l'm gonna ask the Lord for some of
that cash while He's still payin' off.

191
00:15:56,234 --> 00:15:59,635
- Luther, look in on the baby
from time to time, will you ?
- You too, Louise ?

192
00:15:59,704 --> 00:16:01,934
Child, yeah, got to go pray.
See ya.

193
00:16:02,006 --> 00:16:04,270
Hey, Erie.

194
00:16:04,342 --> 00:16:07,709
- Mmm, gimme !
Gimme, gimme, gimme, gimme !
- There's your cut.

195
00:16:07,778 --> 00:16:11,009
- [ Chuckling ]
- Guy turned out to be an oil well.

196
00:16:11,082 --> 00:16:13,949
- Which way'd he go ?
- Due north. He was gonna take it all.

197
00:16:14,018 --> 00:16:17,613
Ah, the bastard.
He can blow his nose all the way.

198
00:16:17,688 --> 00:16:21,317
[ Giggling ]

199
00:16:21,392 --> 00:16:25,089
There you go, Luther.
Six G's.

200
00:16:26,831 --> 00:16:30,198
- You're late. Where you been ?
- l had a couple of appointments.

201
00:16:31,536 --> 00:16:34,733
How much did you lose ?

202
00:16:37,875 --> 00:16:40,776
[ Grunts ]
All of it.

203
00:16:40,845 --> 00:16:43,439
ln one goddamn night ?

204
00:16:43,514 --> 00:16:46,779
What are you spraying money
around like that for ?
You could've been nailed !

205
00:16:46,851 --> 00:16:49,285
l checked the place.
There were no dicks in there.

206
00:16:49,353 --> 00:16:52,880
But you're a con man,
and you blew it like a pimp !
Didn't teach you to be no pimp.

207
00:16:52,957 --> 00:16:56,051
What the hell's eatin' you ?
l've blown money before.

208
00:16:56,127 --> 00:17:00,655
- No class grifter
would've done it, that's all.
- You think my play is bad ?

209
00:17:00,731 --> 00:17:03,097
l think you're the best.

210
00:17:06,504 --> 00:17:09,268
l wouldn't be getting out,
otherwise.

211
00:17:10,641 --> 00:17:12,632
What the hell
are you talkin' about ?

212
00:17:12,710 --> 00:17:14,974
l'm getting too old
for this racket.

213
00:17:15,046 --> 00:17:17,241
You hang on too long
and you start embarrassing yourself.

214
00:17:17,315 --> 00:17:19,840
We just took off on the biggest score
we've ever had.

215
00:17:19,917 --> 00:17:22,647
lt's nothing compared to what you
could be making on the big con.

216
00:17:22,720 --> 00:17:24,915
But you played the big con.

217
00:17:24,989 --> 00:17:29,016
You told me yourself it was some
dumb game for mama's boys and flakes.

218
00:17:29,093 --> 00:17:31,254
[ Laughs ]

219
00:17:31,329 --> 00:17:34,093
Hell, l never played no big con.

220
00:17:34,165 --> 00:17:37,157
l hung around
and picked up a few things.

221
00:17:37,234 --> 00:17:41,603
Ain't no rich boys gonna trust
a hungry nigger enough to be conned.

222
00:17:41,672 --> 00:17:43,936
But l'll tell you,

223
00:17:44,008 --> 00:17:47,273
l've been looking for this one
all my life, Johnny.

224
00:17:47,345 --> 00:17:50,906
Now l have a chance
to step out when l'm ahead.

225
00:17:50,982 --> 00:17:53,815
Come on ! What would
you do with yourself ?

226
00:17:53,884 --> 00:17:57,217
l have a brother in K.C.,
runs a freight outlet.

227
00:17:57,288 --> 00:18:00,052
l can go halfsies with him.

228
00:18:00,124 --> 00:18:03,719
lt ain't too exciting,
but it's mostly legal.

229
00:18:06,497 --> 00:18:09,989
l got an old friend in Chicago
named Henry Gondorff.

230
00:18:10,067 --> 00:18:14,333
l want you to look him up.
There ain't a better inside man alive.

231
00:18:14,405 --> 00:18:18,205
- He'll teach you all you gotta know.
- To hell with that.

232
00:18:18,275 --> 00:18:20,709
l want to work with you, Luther.

233
00:18:20,778 --> 00:18:23,645
l'm out, Johnny.

234
00:18:29,387 --> 00:18:32,823
Yeah, sure.
lf that's the way you want it.

235
00:18:34,191 --> 00:18:36,625
That's the way l want it.

236
00:18:38,529 --> 00:18:42,625
- [ Can Rattling ]
- How do you like that Coleman ?
After five years.

237
00:18:42,700 --> 00:18:47,137
- lt was the only thing to do.
He knew he was holding you back.
- Yeah, but we were partners.

238
00:18:47,204 --> 00:18:50,139
lf it weren't for Luther, l'd still be
hustling pinball at Gianelli's.

239
00:18:50,207 --> 00:18:52,641
l don't need more
than what l got.

240
00:18:52,710 --> 00:18:55,144
You ain't gonna have anything if you
don't lay off the games of chance.

241
00:18:55,212 --> 00:18:58,147
- There's a depression on.
- Yeah, there's always a depression on.

242
00:18:58,215 --> 00:19:01,810
- lf you saved a little, maybe you
wouldn't have to grift so much.
- l like griftin'.

243
00:19:01,886 --> 00:19:04,184
- Maybe you could
buy yourself some things.
- What ?

244
00:19:04,255 --> 00:19:07,156
- New clothes, a car.
- l got clothes, and l
don't know how to drive.

245
00:19:07,224 --> 00:19:10,591
- What else do you got to sell ?
- [ Brakes Screeching ]

246
00:19:10,661 --> 00:19:14,495
Hey, Hooker !
Come on, you son of a--

247
00:19:15,599 --> 00:19:19,194
- Okay. Come on.
- Oh, hi there, Snyder.

248
00:19:19,270 --> 00:19:23,036
What's the matter ? Things a little
slow down at the bunco department ?

249
00:19:23,107 --> 00:19:27,601
- Somebody lose the dominoes ?
- You scored blood money today,
and you need a friend.

250
00:19:27,678 --> 00:19:30,238
Go find yourself
a shoplifter to roll.

251
00:19:33,851 --> 00:19:38,117
You got the wrong guy, pal.
l've been home with the flu all day.

252
00:19:38,189 --> 00:19:40,987
- You can stake out
my toilet if you want.
- Keep talkin' !

253
00:19:54,105 --> 00:19:58,007
- [ Coughs, Spits ]
- l'll tell you what you did, smart boy.

254
00:19:58,075 --> 00:20:02,011
You tied into a loaded mark
on 47th across from Maxie's.

255
00:20:02,079 --> 00:20:06,982
You and Coleman played the switch for
him and blew him off to a cab on 49th.

256
00:20:07,051 --> 00:20:11,920
lf he hadn't been a numbers
runner for Doyle Lonnegan,
it would've been perfect.

257
00:20:11,989 --> 00:20:14,423
You're crazy.

258
00:20:15,860 --> 00:20:18,795
l ain't stupid enough
to play for no racket's money.

259
00:20:18,863 --> 00:20:23,232
Not intentionally, maybe.
That don't cut no ice with Lonnegan.

260
00:20:23,300 --> 00:20:25,962
- He'll swat you like a fly.
- Yeah, well--

261
00:20:27,304 --> 00:20:29,738
l'll square it
with the fixer.

262
00:20:29,807 --> 00:20:33,208
Nobody can buy you a prayer
if l put the finger on you.

263
00:20:33,277 --> 00:20:37,941
Now, l figure your end of the score
was at least three G's.

264
00:20:38,015 --> 00:20:41,451
- l want two, no matter what it was.
- My take was only one.

265
00:20:41,519 --> 00:20:45,785
Then you're gonna have to come up
with another grand somewhere.

266
00:20:55,699 --> 00:20:58,133
All right.

267
00:21:09,413 --> 00:21:12,871
You're a smart egg, Hooker.

268
00:21:12,950 --> 00:21:15,885
No sense getting dead
over two grand.

269
00:21:24,128 --> 00:21:27,120
Relax, Erie.
l'll bill ya.

270
00:21:36,540 --> 00:21:39,532
- l thought you blew all your money.
- l did.

271
00:21:39,610 --> 00:21:42,101
The stuff l gave him
is counterfeit.

272
00:21:42,179 --> 00:21:45,080
They'll spot it the first place
he tries to spend it.

273
00:21:45,149 --> 00:21:47,709
Are you crazy,
giving him counterfeit money ?

274
00:21:48,552 --> 00:21:50,850
Hey ! Wait up !

275
00:21:50,921 --> 00:21:53,355
Where you goin' ?

276
00:21:57,828 --> 00:22:00,092
Aw.

277
00:22:00,164 --> 00:22:02,359
- [ Shouts ]
- Hey, you--

278
00:22:05,636 --> 00:22:07,900
- [ Coin Rattles ]
- [ Phone Dings ]

279
00:22:07,972 --> 00:22:10,964
[ Dialing ]

280
00:22:12,543 --> 00:22:15,979
What the hell are you gonna do
if Snyder puts the finger on you ?

281
00:22:16,046 --> 00:22:18,810
- You're committin' suicide, kid.
- What difference does it make ?

282
00:22:18,883 --> 00:22:23,149
lf Snyder knows about us,
so does everybody else.
He never gets anything first.

283
00:22:23,220 --> 00:22:26,485
Hey, listen to me.
Don't go back to your place tonight.

284
00:22:26,557 --> 00:22:30,084
Don't go anyplace you usually go.
You hear me ?

285
00:22:30,160 --> 00:22:32,822
Damn !
There's no answer at Luther's.

286
00:22:32,897 --> 00:22:36,389
Look, you better get out
of town or something.

287
00:22:36,467 --> 00:22:40,062
- [ Woman Shouting ]
- [ Erie ] Hey, lady, lady, let go !

288
00:22:40,137 --> 00:22:43,868
- Ma'am ! Ma'am ! Hey !
- l want my nickel back
for that telephone !

289
00:22:45,309 --> 00:22:48,403
[ Dog Barking ]

290
00:22:49,980 --> 00:22:53,472
[ Man ]
No, sir. Nobody here did.

291
00:22:53,550 --> 00:22:55,541
1521 North Bryant.

292
00:22:55,619 --> 00:22:58,782
[ Baby Crying ]

293
00:22:58,856 --> 00:23:01,984
- [ People Murmuring ]
- Luther !

294
00:23:13,137 --> 00:23:16,197
- ls he dead ?
- l don't know. There was a big fight.

295
00:23:16,273 --> 00:23:19,299
l don't know.
Somebody must've pushed him.

296
00:23:22,746 --> 00:23:26,341
- Ah, Jesus !
- Luther !

297
00:23:26,417 --> 00:23:28,681
- Luther ! Oh !
- Jesus !

298
00:23:28,752 --> 00:23:31,653
God ! No ! No ! No !
[ Sobbing ]

299
00:23:31,722 --> 00:23:34,589
[ Sobbing ]
Luther ! Luther !

300
00:23:34,658 --> 00:23:38,685
What happened ? God, who would do
such a thing to you, Luther ?

301
00:23:38,762 --> 00:23:42,391
- [ Siren Wailing ]
- Luther ! [ Sobbing ]

302
00:23:42,466 --> 00:23:45,060
Come on. Come on !
Let's get out of here.

303
00:23:45,135 --> 00:23:47,160
- [ Car Tires Screeching ]
- Luther !

304
00:23:47,237 --> 00:23:50,866
Come on ! lf Snyder
catches you here, you're dead !

305
00:23:50,941 --> 00:23:53,466
Talk to me, honey !
Say something !

306
00:23:53,544 --> 00:23:56,240
- Get outta here !
- [ Officer ] Outta the way.

307
00:23:56,313 --> 00:23:58,440
Help me, help me, help me !

308
00:23:58,515 --> 00:24:01,177
[ Sobbing Continues ]

309
00:24:20,037 --> 00:24:23,131
[ Car Horn Honking ]

310
00:24:28,645 --> 00:24:31,079
[ Car Horn Honks ]

311
00:24:36,120 --> 00:24:38,554
[ Car Horn Honks ]

312
00:24:44,261 --> 00:24:47,662
Uh... excuse me.

313
00:24:47,731 --> 00:24:51,258
l'm looking for a guy named
Henry Gondorff. You know him ?

314
00:24:51,335 --> 00:24:53,929
No.

315
00:24:57,441 --> 00:24:59,500
You sure ?

316
00:24:59,576 --> 00:25:02,443
- Beat it.
- Luther Coleman sent me.

317
00:25:06,116 --> 00:25:08,778
- Are you Hooker ?
- Yeah.

318
00:25:10,421 --> 00:25:12,889
Why didn't you say so ?

319
00:25:14,258 --> 00:25:17,659
We heard about Luther last night.
Come on.

320
00:25:25,202 --> 00:25:27,693
l thought maybe you were a cop
or something.

321
00:25:27,771 --> 00:25:30,535
lt's the room in the back.

322
00:25:30,607 --> 00:25:34,168
He wasn't expecting you
so soon, though.

323
00:25:34,244 --> 00:25:36,735
Thanks.

324
00:25:58,936 --> 00:26:02,269
[ Train Rumbling Overhead ]

325
00:26:05,809 --> 00:26:09,245
[ Rumbling Grows Louder ]

326
00:26:20,924 --> 00:26:23,859
[ Rumbling Stops ]

327
00:26:26,296 --> 00:26:28,856
[ Snoring ]

328
00:26:30,033 --> 00:26:33,093
[ Snoring Continues ]

329
00:26:37,341 --> 00:26:40,469
[ Snoring ]

330
00:26:42,079 --> 00:26:45,048
The great Henry Gondorff.

331
00:26:46,216 --> 00:26:49,310
Turn it off !

332
00:26:51,421 --> 00:26:53,753
You sober ?

333
00:26:53,824 --> 00:26:56,418
Turn it off, will ya ?

334
00:27:06,436 --> 00:27:08,666
[ Sighs ]

335
00:27:10,207 --> 00:27:12,368
[ Sighs ]

336
00:27:12,442 --> 00:27:15,377
Glad to meet you, kid.
You're a real horse's ass.

337
00:27:15,445 --> 00:27:18,778
Luther said l could learn
something from you.

338
00:27:20,184 --> 00:27:23,779
l already know how to drink.

339
00:27:23,854 --> 00:27:26,186
Sorry about Luther.

340
00:27:26,256 --> 00:27:29,851
He was the best street worker
l ever saw.

341
00:27:31,828 --> 00:27:35,696
He had you down as a big timer.
What happened ?

342
00:27:39,169 --> 00:27:42,605
l conned a senator from Florida
on a stock deal.

343
00:27:42,673 --> 00:27:46,268
A real lop-ear; thought he was gonna
take over General Electric.

344
00:27:46,343 --> 00:27:49,506
Some chanteusie woke him, though,
and he put the feds on me.

345
00:27:49,580 --> 00:27:52,572
You mean you blew it.

346
00:27:52,649 --> 00:27:55,675
Luther didn't tell me
you had a big mouth.

347
00:27:55,752 --> 00:27:59,188
He didn't tell me
you was a screwup either.

348
00:28:01,825 --> 00:28:04,191
[ Feet Sloshing ]

349
00:28:07,164 --> 00:28:10,429
You played any big cons
since then ?

350
00:28:10,500 --> 00:28:15,528
l lammed around a bunch of bohunk towns,
one kick ahead of the G-men.

351
00:28:15,606 --> 00:28:19,235
Would be still,
if Billie hadn't set me up here.

352
00:28:22,312 --> 00:28:25,577
Don't kid yourself, friend.
l still know how.

353
00:28:31,121 --> 00:28:35,080
You gonna stay for breakfast,
or do you already know how to eat ?

354
00:28:36,994 --> 00:28:39,929
l picked something up
along the way.

355
00:28:43,634 --> 00:28:46,125
ls Lonnegan after you too ?

356
00:28:46,203 --> 00:28:48,728
l don't know.
l ain't seen anybody.

357
00:28:48,805 --> 00:28:51,706
You never do, kid.

358
00:28:51,775 --> 00:28:54,243
[ Water Stops Running ]

359
00:28:54,311 --> 00:28:57,803
[ Gondorff Groans ]

360
00:28:57,881 --> 00:29:00,509
[ Water Bubbling ]

361
00:29:04,721 --> 00:29:07,281
Doyle ?

362
00:29:07,357 --> 00:29:09,416
Yeah.

363
00:29:11,361 --> 00:29:15,821
We just talked to Chicago. They got one
of the grifters last night-- a nigger.

364
00:29:17,401 --> 00:29:22,134
- How about the other one ?
- They're still looking for him.

365
00:29:22,205 --> 00:29:26,005
- Who did Combs put on it ?
- He gave it to Riley and Cole.

366
00:29:26,076 --> 00:29:29,204
They staked out the other guy's place
last night, but he never showed.

367
00:29:29,279 --> 00:29:31,804
They figure maybe
he skipped town.

368
00:29:31,882 --> 00:29:34,442
You wanna keep after him ?

369
00:29:34,518 --> 00:29:37,453
You see that fella
in the red sweater ?

370
00:29:37,521 --> 00:29:39,614
His name's Danny McCoy.

371
00:29:39,690 --> 00:29:43,490
Works a few of the protection
rackets for Canarro when he's
waiting for something better.

372
00:29:43,560 --> 00:29:47,496
Danny and l have known each other
since we were six.

373
00:29:49,599 --> 00:29:53,091
Take a good look
at that face, Floyd.

374
00:29:53,170 --> 00:29:57,197
Because if he ever finds out
l can be beat by one lousy grifter,

375
00:29:57,274 --> 00:30:00,209
l'll have to kill him
and every other hood...

376
00:30:00,277 --> 00:30:04,338
who wants to muscle in
on my Chicago operation.

377
00:30:04,414 --> 00:30:07,008
- You follow ?
- Yes, sir.

378
00:30:08,585 --> 00:30:10,780
Good lad.

379
00:30:13,824 --> 00:30:18,158
- You feeling all right
this morning, Henry ?
- Yeah, fine.

380
00:30:18,228 --> 00:30:21,163
You mind opening up the round
a little early today ?

381
00:30:21,231 --> 00:30:24,166
- We got some business
coming in before hours.
- Sure.

382
00:30:24,234 --> 00:30:26,498
And check the main gearing,
will ya ?

383
00:30:26,570 --> 00:30:30,233
Man O' War started rattling yesterday
and threw a kid on its head.

384
00:30:30,307 --> 00:30:32,673
[ Clicks Tongue ]

385
00:30:32,743 --> 00:30:36,679
Great little countess, that Billie.
She runs a spiffy house up there too.

386
00:30:36,747 --> 00:30:41,514
- You plan to spend
the rest of your life here ?
- l could do a lot worse.

387
00:30:46,757 --> 00:30:50,921
- Listen, am l gonna learn
to play the big con or not ?
- What's your hurry ?

388
00:30:50,994 --> 00:30:54,555
- l wanna play for Lonnegan.
- You know anything about the guy ?

389
00:30:54,631 --> 00:30:57,566
Yeah, he croaked Luther.
Anything else l gotta know ?

390
00:31:02,873 --> 00:31:06,138
[ Sighs ]

391
00:31:06,209 --> 00:31:09,474
All right. He runs a numbers racket
on the South Side.

392
00:31:09,546 --> 00:31:12,379
He owns a packinghouse,
a few banks--

393
00:31:12,449 --> 00:31:15,282
Yeah, and half the politicians
in New York and Chicago.

394
00:31:15,352 --> 00:31:18,287
Not a fix in this world is gonna
cool him out if he blows on you.

395
00:31:18,355 --> 00:31:20,789
- l'll get him anyway.
- Why ?

396
00:31:20,857 --> 00:31:25,294
'Cause l don't know enough
about killing to kill him.

397
00:31:25,362 --> 00:31:28,854
[ Train Rumbling ]

398
00:31:41,511 --> 00:31:43,843
You can't do it alone, you know.

399
00:31:43,914 --> 00:31:46,508
lt takes a mob of guys like you
and enough money to make 'em look good.

400
00:31:46,583 --> 00:31:49,017
- l know plenty of guys.
- lt's not like playing winos
in the street.

401
00:31:49,085 --> 00:31:50,916
- You can't outrun Lonnegan.
- l never played for no winos.

402
00:31:50,987 --> 00:31:54,787
You gotta keep his con
even after you take his money.
He can't know you took him.

403
00:31:54,858 --> 00:31:58,294
- You're scared of him.
- Right down to my socks, buster.

404
00:31:58,361 --> 00:32:01,296
You're talking about a guy
who'd kill a grifter...

405
00:32:01,364 --> 00:32:04,731
over a chunk of money
wouldn't support him for two days.

406
00:32:06,102 --> 00:32:08,536
You're gonna go for him.

407
00:32:10,874 --> 00:32:14,139
Just don't want a hothead looking to
get even, coming back halfway through,

408
00:32:14,211 --> 00:32:18,011
saying, ''lt ain't enough,''
'cause it's all we're gonna get.

409
00:32:21,985 --> 00:32:24,249
Can you get a mob together ?

410
00:32:24,321 --> 00:32:27,688
After what happened to Luther,
l don't think l can get more
than two, three hundred guys.

411
00:32:27,757 --> 00:32:32,285
.. [ Calliope ]

412
00:32:32,362 --> 00:32:36,355
Luther said you learn fast.
l hope he's right.

413
00:32:39,669 --> 00:32:43,002
.. [ Piano: Ragtime ]

414
00:35:02,012 --> 00:35:02,412
.. [ Calliope ]

415
00:35:02,412 --> 00:35:05,779
.. [ Calliope ]

416
00:35:08,018 --> 00:35:10,452
Lonnegan gets most of his income
from the numbers,

417
00:35:10,520 --> 00:35:13,614
even though he's been putting more money
into his savings and loan business.

418
00:35:13,690 --> 00:35:16,124
- [ Gondorff ] Think he's
moving out of the racket ?
- No.

419
00:35:16,192 --> 00:35:18,456
He owns most of the stock,
and it's traded.

420
00:35:18,528 --> 00:35:21,122
My guess is he's just trying
to build himself a respectable image.

421
00:35:21,197 --> 00:35:25,395
He came out of Five Points,
but he's been telling everybody
he was born in Forest Hills.

422
00:35:25,468 --> 00:35:29,199
He knows the market, though. l don't
think we can take him on a stocks deal.

423
00:35:29,272 --> 00:35:31,206
Twist, what about the numbers ?

424
00:35:31,274 --> 00:35:35,574
Tipsters say it's run
out of a packinghouse
on 14th by a guy named Combs.

425
00:35:35,645 --> 00:35:38,910
Lonnegan comes out every three weeks
or so to check on it, but...

426
00:35:38,982 --> 00:35:42,213
he stays away from the day-to-day stuff
in case it's raided.

427
00:35:42,285 --> 00:35:45,254
These are two of Combs's
favorite torpedoes: Riley and Cole.

428
00:35:45,321 --> 00:35:48,313
You ever seen 'em ?

429
00:35:48,391 --> 00:35:50,325
No.

430
00:35:50,393 --> 00:35:53,021
They're the ones
who hit Luther.

431
00:35:53,096 --> 00:35:56,532
They also got the numbers runner
you conned: a guy named Mottola.

432
00:35:56,599 --> 00:35:59,932
Found him in a quarry
with a knife in his eye.

433
00:36:00,003 --> 00:36:03,200
Lonnegan's had seven or eight people
rubbed on his way up.

434
00:36:03,273 --> 00:36:06,208
His pattern has been
to get close to a racket boss,

435
00:36:06,276 --> 00:36:08,870
learn the operation,
then move in on it.

436
00:36:08,945 --> 00:36:12,881
He's done it to Gorman,
O'Donnell, Buchalman;
took the numbers from Sharkey.

437
00:36:12,949 --> 00:36:17,283
All four of these guys are dead.
He's vindictive as hell, Henry.

438
00:36:17,353 --> 00:36:21,619
Kills for pride. Doesn't add up
he'd let Hooker get away from him.

439
00:36:21,691 --> 00:36:25,127
You see anything, kid,
you let us know.

440
00:36:25,195 --> 00:36:28,790
lf they put you on the spot,
we gotta fold the con. You got that ?

441
00:36:28,865 --> 00:36:32,562
Yeah. You sure it's gotta
be one of these two guys ?

442
00:36:32,635 --> 00:36:35,968
Nope. They're just
the only ones we know of.

443
00:36:38,274 --> 00:36:40,208
Okay.

444
00:36:40,276 --> 00:36:43,541
.. [ Calliope Continues ]

445
00:36:47,450 --> 00:36:49,714
Time.

446
00:36:51,621 --> 00:36:54,590
[ People Chattering, Laughing ]

447
00:36:59,562 --> 00:37:02,929
Set me up five more beers,
will you, Danny ?

448
00:37:06,002 --> 00:37:08,664
.. [ Humming ]

449
00:37:11,574 --> 00:37:14,441
- You the owner here ?
- That's right.

450
00:37:14,511 --> 00:37:17,173
Lt. Snyder, Bunco.

451
00:37:17,247 --> 00:37:21,411
That's a Joliet badge, Snyder.
Don't cut much up here.

452
00:37:21,484 --> 00:37:24,453
Looking for a guy on the lam
from a counterfeiting rap.
Thought he might've come here.

453
00:37:24,521 --> 00:37:28,116
Don't think so.
l know everyone in the place,
and l always bounce the lamsters.

454
00:37:28,191 --> 00:37:30,625
All right
if l look around in here ?

455
00:37:30,693 --> 00:37:34,459
No, but you're welcome
to a free beer before you go.

456
00:37:41,437 --> 00:37:44,201
l don't really need
your permission.

457
00:37:47,944 --> 00:37:50,378
l don't know what to do
with this guy.

458
00:37:50,446 --> 00:37:53,643
He's an lrishman who doesn't drink,
doesn't smoke and doesn't chase dames.

459
00:37:53,716 --> 00:37:56,150
He's a grand knight
in the Knights of Columbus,

460
00:37:56,219 --> 00:37:58,153
and he only goes out
to play faro.

461
00:37:58,221 --> 00:38:01,054
Sometimes plays 15, 20 hours at a time;
just him against the house.

462
00:38:01,124 --> 00:38:03,319
- Roulette, craps ?
- He won't touch 'em.

463
00:38:03,393 --> 00:38:06,829
The croupier at Gilman's says
he never plays anything he can't win.

464
00:38:06,896 --> 00:38:09,922
- Sports ?
- He likes to be seen
with fighters sometimes,

465
00:38:09,999 --> 00:38:12,797
but he doesn't go
to the fights or bet on 'em.

466
00:38:12,869 --> 00:38:17,135
- Jesus. Does he do anything
where he's not alone ?
- Just poker.

467
00:38:18,908 --> 00:38:21,672
And he cheats.

468
00:38:21,744 --> 00:38:24,178
Pretty good at it too.

469
00:38:29,018 --> 00:38:31,248
Where does he play ?

470
00:38:31,321 --> 00:38:34,256
The porters say he runs a braced game
on the Century Limited...

471
00:38:34,324 --> 00:38:36,588
when he comes out here
from New York.

472
00:38:36,659 --> 00:38:38,752
$100 minimum, straight poker.

473
00:38:38,828 --> 00:38:41,820
A lot of high rollers ride that train
just to play him.

474
00:38:41,898 --> 00:38:44,731
That sounds good, J.J.

475
00:38:44,801 --> 00:38:47,497
[ Laughter, lndistinct Chatter ]

476
00:38:50,306 --> 00:38:52,570
Which way are the rooms ?

477
00:38:52,642 --> 00:38:55,475
- Who told you this guy was in here ?
- Nobody.

478
00:38:55,545 --> 00:38:57,979
l just know what kind of woman
he likes.

479
00:38:58,047 --> 00:39:00,481
l'm gonna check all the joy houses
'til l find him.

480
00:39:00,550 --> 00:39:02,916
Maybe l could help you
if you tell me his name.

481
00:39:02,986 --> 00:39:06,217
l doubt it.
Which way are the rooms ?

482
00:39:06,289 --> 00:39:09,918
Right through there. But l
wouldn't go in there if l were you.

483
00:39:09,993 --> 00:39:14,123
- What are you gonna do, call the cops ?
- l don't have to.

484
00:39:14,197 --> 00:39:18,190
You'd be busting in on
the chief of police just up the hall.

485
00:39:19,335 --> 00:39:22,532
.. [ Calliope ]

486
00:39:27,844 --> 00:39:30,813
[ Banker ] We'll play it out here.
A huge duke is too simple.

487
00:39:30,880 --> 00:39:33,815
With no fix, we're gonna need a con
with a surefire blow-off.

488
00:39:33,883 --> 00:39:36,317
[ J.J. ] l think we ought to
play this guy on the payoff.

489
00:39:36,386 --> 00:39:39,150
lt's the tightest game we got,
and it's not all over the papers yet.

490
00:39:39,222 --> 00:39:42,953
Lonnegan is a fast egg. He's not going
to sit still for a standard play.

491
00:39:43,026 --> 00:39:46,757
[ Banker ] What does that leave us ?
We can't con the payoff to a banker.

492
00:39:46,829 --> 00:39:50,788
We'll use the wire.
Haven't known a poker player
didn't wanna beat the ponies.

493
00:39:50,867 --> 00:39:54,667
- The wire's been out of date
for ten years.
- That's why he won't know it.

494
00:39:54,737 --> 00:39:56,932
l'm not sure l know it.

495
00:39:57,006 --> 00:39:59,497
lt'll take two of us
working the inside.

496
00:39:59,575 --> 00:40:02,544
Any objections to Hooker
as second man ?

497
00:40:04,948 --> 00:40:08,884
All right. We'll give Lonnegan
the hook on the train and play him here.

498
00:40:08,952 --> 00:40:11,682
J.J., you think l can get
in that poker game ?

499
00:40:11,754 --> 00:40:14,689
All you gotta do is show up with
a lot of money and look like a sucker.

500
00:40:14,757 --> 00:40:16,850
l also gotta win.

501
00:40:16,926 --> 00:40:21,556
By the way, any of you guys
been passing bad money lately ?

502
00:40:24,567 --> 00:40:27,798
lf he comes in again,
stall him so l can get a look at him.

503
00:40:27,870 --> 00:40:30,134
[ Billie ]
Mm-hmm.

504
00:40:41,584 --> 00:40:44,678
Fella by the name of Stenner had
this place 'til about six months ago,

505
00:40:44,754 --> 00:40:47,188
but he had to give it up.

506
00:40:47,256 --> 00:40:51,022
lt doesn't look so good, but maybe you
can fix it up a little bit.

507
00:40:51,094 --> 00:40:55,030
Watch your step when you come in.
There's a dip down to the left.

508
00:41:09,579 --> 00:41:12,514
- How does it look, Eddie ?
- lt looks all right, Kid.

509
00:41:12,582 --> 00:41:15,346
lt's big enough,
and it's off the street.

510
00:41:15,418 --> 00:41:19,354
lt's kind of short notice. l'm not sure
we can get it done by Saturday.

511
00:41:19,422 --> 00:41:23,950
Got to. Gondorff's riding the mark down
from New York on the Century.

512
00:41:24,027 --> 00:41:27,292
We'll take it. That building at the end
of the alley, do you manage that ?

513
00:41:27,363 --> 00:41:30,298
- For 15 years.
- l'll need a corner room
facing this way.

514
00:41:30,366 --> 00:41:32,800
- How much a week ?
- Only rents by the month.

515
00:41:32,869 --> 00:41:35,736
Two hundred and fifty
for the two of them.

516
00:41:35,805 --> 00:41:39,502
- Last time l expect
to see you down here.
- Never heard of the place.

517
00:41:39,575 --> 00:41:42,271
[ Old Man ] lt's been a while
since l stocked a wire store.

518
00:41:42,345 --> 00:41:44,609
Not many mobs
playing that anymore.

519
00:41:44,680 --> 00:41:47,114
[ Eddie ] All we'll need
is the bookie setup for now.

520
00:41:47,183 --> 00:41:50,516
[ Old Man ] l'll rent you everything
l got in the warehouse for two grand.

521
00:41:50,586 --> 00:41:54,852
That'll give you phones, cages,
blackboards and ticker gear.

522
00:41:54,924 --> 00:41:58,018
lf you want a counter and bar,
that's another grand.

523
00:41:58,094 --> 00:42:01,860
-That's pretty steep, Benny.
-[ Benny ] Gondorff's still a hot item.

524
00:42:01,931 --> 00:42:04,900
- Where would l be if he gets hit ?
- Just give us what you can.

525
00:42:04,967 --> 00:42:08,835
We'll send a truck. How do you want to
work this ? Flat rate or percentage ?

526
00:42:08,905 --> 00:42:11,339
- Who's the mark ?
- Doyle Lonnegan.

527
00:42:15,044 --> 00:42:17,205
Flat rate.

528
00:42:32,228 --> 00:42:35,595
The guy in the black hat
with the gimp.

529
00:42:44,240 --> 00:42:46,731
He's not as tough as he thinks.

530
00:42:46,809 --> 00:42:48,743
Neither are we.

531
00:42:52,715 --> 00:42:54,706
- Mr. Shaw ?
- Right.

532
00:42:54,784 --> 00:42:56,718
You wanted to see me ?

533
00:42:56,786 --> 00:42:59,516
l hear there's a friendly poker game on
this train. You know anything about it ?

534
00:42:59,589 --> 00:43:01,523
- Oh, a little.
- Thank you, sir.

535
00:43:01,591 --> 00:43:04,185
- Can you get me in that game ?
- Oh, l don't know.

536
00:43:04,260 --> 00:43:06,524
There's usually
a waiting list.

537
00:43:09,866 --> 00:43:12,198
That'll get you
first alternate, sir.

538
00:43:17,840 --> 00:43:19,774
l'll see what l can do.

539
00:43:22,945 --> 00:43:24,970
- [ Men Chattering ]
- Hey, Twist !

540
00:43:25,047 --> 00:43:27,413
Patty, me boy !
How are you ?

541
00:43:27,483 --> 00:43:30,475
- How are you, Twist ?
- Hey, Champ, you're
lookin' like a million !

542
00:43:30,553 --> 00:43:32,487
- Yeah, so do you.
- Good to see you !

543
00:43:32,555 --> 00:43:35,149
Goldie, you old
son of a gun. Hey !

544
00:43:35,224 --> 00:43:38,250
l saw the Kid in Denver.
He says to say hello to you.

545
00:43:38,327 --> 00:43:42,559
- Joiner, are you still
workin' those shapes ?
- Any number you want, Twist !

546
00:43:42,632 --> 00:43:45,226
- Good to see you again.
- Okay, Lacey. Good to see you.

547
00:43:45,301 --> 00:43:48,429
- lt's good to see you. Come on in !
- Dukey, how are you ?

548
00:43:48,504 --> 00:43:51,496
- When did you get back in town ?
- A couple of days ago.

549
00:43:51,574 --> 00:43:53,906
You heard about Luther Coleman,
didn't you ?

550
00:43:53,976 --> 00:43:56,911
Yeah. Some of the boys were
passin' the hat for Alva and the kids.

551
00:43:56,979 --> 00:44:00,847
- l never seen the guys so worked up.
- Don't worry about it, Dukey.

552
00:44:00,917 --> 00:44:03,579
We're gonna send a little
calling card of our own.

553
00:44:03,653 --> 00:44:05,883
Gondorff is setting up
a wire store.

554
00:44:05,955 --> 00:44:07,889
l'm gonna need
a 20-man boost right away.

555
00:44:07,957 --> 00:44:11,222
l got plenty of talent out there
tonight. Take your pick. Lace !

556
00:44:11,294 --> 00:44:15,025
This is a tough one.
These boys have got to be the quill.

557
00:44:15,097 --> 00:44:18,760
Get me the sheet.
Let's see who's in town, huh ?

558
00:44:18,834 --> 00:44:21,200
Hey, Patty,
give me the sheet.

559
00:44:21,270 --> 00:44:24,205
- Sure.
- [ Door Opens ]

560
00:44:32,515 --> 00:44:34,949
[ Chattering Stops ]

561
00:44:38,988 --> 00:44:41,081
Gondorff's already on--

562
00:44:49,832 --> 00:44:52,096
Twist, you know this guy ?

563
00:44:56,305 --> 00:44:59,832
No, l never saw him before.
He's a dick, though.

564
00:45:10,086 --> 00:45:12,247
Hello, Snyder.

565
00:45:12,321 --> 00:45:15,347
- What are you doin' up here ?
- l'm on vacation.

566
00:45:15,424 --> 00:45:18,018
Hey, you seen that friend
of yours lately ?

567
00:45:18,094 --> 00:45:20,028
No, no.
He, uh, packed it in.

568
00:45:20,096 --> 00:45:24,032
- Enrolled in detective school.
- [ Laughing ]

569
00:45:27,003 --> 00:45:30,131
- [ Grunts ]
- [ Glass Breaks ]

570
00:45:30,206 --> 00:45:32,140
lf you see him,

571
00:45:32,208 --> 00:45:35,974
you tell him he better pay up
before l get to him.

572
00:45:45,688 --> 00:45:47,622
That son of a bitch.

573
00:45:50,326 --> 00:45:52,260
Ah, thanks, Lace.

574
00:45:52,328 --> 00:45:54,262
Let's see what we got here.

575
00:45:54,330 --> 00:45:56,821
Let's see, Horse Face Lee,
Slim Miller,

576
00:45:56,899 --> 00:46:01,063
Suitcase Murphy and the Big Alabama
are in from New Orleans.

577
00:46:01,137 --> 00:46:03,901
Cryin' Jonesy and the Boone Kid
from Denver.

578
00:46:03,973 --> 00:46:07,807
Dippy Burke and Limehouse Chappie
from New York.

579
00:46:07,877 --> 00:46:11,836
Well, these and the guys outside should
give you 30 or more to choose from.

580
00:46:11,914 --> 00:46:13,848
Good, Dukey.

581
00:46:13,916 --> 00:46:16,714
Have them down at Stenner's
old pool hall before 6:00.

582
00:46:16,786 --> 00:46:20,847
- We're gonna run the route tonight.
- Okay, Twist, but...

583
00:46:20,923 --> 00:46:24,017
if this thing blows up, remember,
l can't do you no good downtown.

584
00:46:24,093 --> 00:46:26,027
Gondorff is federal.

585
00:46:26,095 --> 00:46:28,757
Dukey, if this thing blows up,

586
00:46:28,831 --> 00:46:31,459
the feds will be
the least of our problems.

587
00:46:34,270 --> 00:46:36,704
[ Whistle Blows ]

588
00:46:39,508 --> 00:46:42,272
[ Whistle Continues ]

589
00:46:42,345 --> 00:46:44,370
[ Train Crossing Bell Ringing ]

590
00:46:46,582 --> 00:46:48,516
- [ Knocking ]
- Yeah ?

591
00:46:52,154 --> 00:46:54,588
- You in ?
- Yeah, l think so.

592
00:46:54,657 --> 00:46:57,319
- l gave the kayducer a C-note.
Did you find out the deck ?
- Mm-hmm.

593
00:46:57,393 --> 00:47:00,328
He usually plays with a Tallyho Fan
or a Tallyho Circle.

594
00:47:00,396 --> 00:47:05,663
l got you one of each. He likes to
cold deck low, eights or nines.

595
00:47:05,735 --> 00:47:08,397
That's nice work, J.J. Here.

596
00:47:21,417 --> 00:47:23,851
[ Train Whistle Blows ]

597
00:47:31,927 --> 00:47:34,259
- Oh, l'm sorry.
- Don't mention it, mum.

598
00:47:55,050 --> 00:47:57,985
[ Man Talking, lndistinct ]

599
00:48:00,790 --> 00:48:04,851
- He'd like to join us.
- Yes, Clyde is a member of our firm.

600
00:48:09,799 --> 00:48:11,733
[ Door Slides Opens ]

601
00:48:27,516 --> 00:48:30,110
She picked him clean.
He never missed it.

602
00:48:31,687 --> 00:48:34,656
My God, it looks like
he's expecting a big night.

603
00:48:34,723 --> 00:48:37,123
Must be 15, 20 grand here.

604
00:48:38,227 --> 00:48:40,161
He's waiting for you
in the card room.

605
00:48:40,229 --> 00:48:42,697
Let him wait.

606
00:49:26,909 --> 00:49:30,436
- [ Train Whistle Blows ]
- Just worry about your end, kid.

607
00:49:30,513 --> 00:49:33,243
lf we ever get to it.

608
00:49:33,315 --> 00:49:37,251
- [ All Laughing ]
- Excuse me.

609
00:49:37,319 --> 00:49:39,446
You sure you checked
this guy out ?

610
00:49:39,522 --> 00:49:41,956
He seemed like a pleasant man;
a lot of cash on him.

611
00:49:42,024 --> 00:49:44,959
Two-hundred-dollar suit,
expensive luggage. l'll vouch for him.

612
00:49:45,027 --> 00:49:46,961
Why isn't he here then ?

613
00:49:47,029 --> 00:49:50,487
- Don't worry. He'll be here.
- All right.

614
00:50:00,943 --> 00:50:02,877
What're you doin' ?

615
00:50:05,447 --> 00:50:10,578
Always drink gin with a mark, kid.
He can't tell if you cut it.

616
00:50:10,653 --> 00:50:13,588
- Two thousand for you, Mr. Clayton ?
- Thank you.

617
00:50:13,656 --> 00:50:16,318
All right, gentlemen.
Should we not wait for him ?

618
00:50:16,392 --> 00:50:18,622
- Let's go.
- l think that's a good idea.

619
00:50:18,694 --> 00:50:20,628
Mr. Clemens, give me the cards.

620
00:50:24,934 --> 00:50:27,528
[ lnhales Deeply, Blows Out ]

621
00:50:29,772 --> 00:50:31,763
Sorry l'm late, guys.
l was takin' a crap.

622
00:50:31,840 --> 00:50:34,604
- [ Door Slams ]
- The name's Shaw.

623
00:50:34,677 --> 00:50:38,670
- Mr. Shaw,
meet Mr. Jameson from Chicago.
- How are ya ?

624
00:50:38,747 --> 00:50:41,045
- Mr. Lombard from Philadelphia.
- Yeah !

625
00:50:41,116 --> 00:50:43,778
- And Mr. Lonnegan from New York.
- Pleased to meet you.

626
00:50:43,852 --> 00:50:45,979
Mr. Clayton, Pittsburgh.

627
00:50:46,055 --> 00:50:50,389
Any of you guys want to make a little
book in Chicago, l'm the guy to see.

628
00:50:50,459 --> 00:50:52,393
Game is straight poker,

629
00:50:52,461 --> 00:50:54,793
$100 minimum, table stakes.

630
00:50:56,865 --> 00:50:59,060
Uh, Mr. Shaw,
this is a gentleman's game.

631
00:50:59,134 --> 00:51:02,535
We assume you're all good
for your debts.

632
00:51:02,605 --> 00:51:06,006
- How much would you like, Mr. Shaw ?
- l'll start with 5,000.

633
00:51:11,313 --> 00:51:13,804
Mr. Shaw, we usually require
a tie at this table.

634
00:51:13,882 --> 00:51:16,180
lf you don't have one,
we can get you one.

635
00:51:16,251 --> 00:51:18,947
Hey, that'd be real nice of you,
Mr. Lonneman.

636
00:51:19,021 --> 00:51:20,784
Lonnegan.

637
00:51:20,856 --> 00:51:23,324
[ Burps ]

638
00:51:26,228 --> 00:51:28,162
[ Man Yelling ]

639
00:51:36,171 --> 00:51:39,607
Name's Curly Jackson.
Worked for Gad Bryan outta Baltimore.

640
00:51:39,675 --> 00:51:42,109
Jackson ?

641
00:51:42,177 --> 00:51:44,771
Jackson, Jackson.
Oh, yeah.

642
00:51:44,847 --> 00:51:47,008
Ever play the wire, Curly ?

643
00:51:47,082 --> 00:51:51,041
Roped for it long ago. l can shill,
mark board, anything you want.

644
00:51:51,120 --> 00:51:53,714
l don't run with riffraff,
and l only drink on weekends.

645
00:51:54,823 --> 00:51:57,383
Me specialty's an Englishman.

646
00:51:59,094 --> 00:52:02,757
We got a rack of suits over there.
Pick yourself a nice tweed one.

647
00:52:02,831 --> 00:52:05,857
That's all right.
l've got all my own stuff.

648
00:52:05,934 --> 00:52:08,164
[ Chuckles ]

649
00:52:11,473 --> 00:52:13,941
Doyle ?

650
00:52:14,009 --> 00:52:15,943
One.

651
00:52:16,011 --> 00:52:18,036
Bill ?

652
00:52:18,113 --> 00:52:20,047
l'll take one.

653
00:52:21,250 --> 00:52:23,184
- Shaw ?
- Three.

654
00:52:25,320 --> 00:52:28,483
And the dealer will take one.

655
00:52:33,896 --> 00:52:35,830
Bet 500.

656
00:52:37,700 --> 00:52:40,032
l'll call.

657
00:52:41,303 --> 00:52:44,431
Call and raise.

658
00:52:44,506 --> 00:52:46,440
- Three hundred.
- [ Jameson ] l'm out.

659
00:52:46,508 --> 00:52:48,442
[ Lombard ]
Fold.

660
00:52:52,347 --> 00:52:54,281
Your three...

661
00:52:55,350 --> 00:52:58,342
and raise... 500.

662
00:53:00,589 --> 00:53:02,523
That's eight to me.

663
00:53:06,995 --> 00:53:08,929
Call.

664
00:53:11,934 --> 00:53:14,562
Jacks on top.

665
00:53:14,636 --> 00:53:16,570
Beats me.

666
00:53:19,374 --> 00:53:21,740
Three tens.

667
00:53:26,715 --> 00:53:28,649
Tough luck, Lonnihan.

668
00:53:28,717 --> 00:53:31,481
But that's what you get
for playing with your head up your ass.

669
00:53:31,553 --> 00:53:34,784
Couple more like that,
we can all go to bed early.

670
00:53:36,325 --> 00:53:39,488
The name's Lonnegan.
Doyle Lonnegan.

671
00:53:39,561 --> 00:53:42,655
You're gonna remember that,
Mr. Shaw, or you're gonna
get yourself another game.

672
00:53:43,866 --> 00:53:45,800
You follow ?

673
00:53:51,540 --> 00:53:53,667
Bring it right up here !

674
00:53:55,511 --> 00:53:58,878
Hey, Eddie, we brought you a tap
into Moe Anenberg's wire.

675
00:53:58,947 --> 00:54:03,179
You'll get race results, odds,
scratches, pole positions, everything.

676
00:54:03,252 --> 00:54:05,686
And just as fast
as Western Union gets 'em.

677
00:54:05,754 --> 00:54:09,952
- Does J.J. know how to use that thing ?
- All he's gotta do is read.

678
00:54:13,061 --> 00:54:15,928
The name is Joe Erie.
[ Sniffles ]

679
00:54:15,998 --> 00:54:17,932
Joe Erie.

680
00:54:19,835 --> 00:54:22,702
You, uh, played
for any particular mobs ?

681
00:54:22,771 --> 00:54:24,568
No.

682
00:54:24,640 --> 00:54:27,108
- You ever play the wire before, Erie ?
- No.

683
00:54:28,744 --> 00:54:32,305
l never played
no big con before, but, uh,

684
00:54:32,381 --> 00:54:35,839
Luther Coleman was a friend of mine,
and l thought maybe...

685
00:54:35,918 --> 00:54:37,852
there'd be somethin'
l could do.

686
00:54:39,721 --> 00:54:41,951
You get that nose
in Duke Boudreau's tonight ?

687
00:54:45,727 --> 00:54:47,661
Yeah.

688
00:54:49,598 --> 00:54:53,056
You got moxie, Erie.
Get yourself a suit.

689
00:54:54,303 --> 00:54:56,635
Thanks.

690
00:54:58,607 --> 00:55:00,541
[ Sneezes Loudly ]

691
00:55:00,609 --> 00:55:04,272
[ Groans, Sniffles ]

692
00:55:04,346 --> 00:55:06,280
l'll bet three.

693
00:55:07,015 --> 00:55:08,949
Call and raise 200.

694
00:55:10,853 --> 00:55:13,344
- [ Snorts ]
- [ Lombard ] Call.

695
00:55:15,157 --> 00:55:17,853
- No.
- [ Clayton ] l'm out.

696
00:55:17,926 --> 00:55:20,258
Call.

697
00:55:20,329 --> 00:55:22,854
Aces over.

698
00:55:22,931 --> 00:55:24,990
Three cowboys.

699
00:55:25,067 --> 00:55:28,036
All red, queen high.

700
00:55:28,103 --> 00:55:31,630
- Well, that finishes me.
- Don't worry about it, pal.

701
00:55:33,141 --> 00:55:35,575
They wouldn't have let you in here
if you weren't a chump !

702
00:55:35,644 --> 00:55:38,306
Lombard'll be joining you
in a couple of minutes.

703
00:55:38,380 --> 00:55:40,974
- Now, look here, Shaw--
- l've had enough of this game...

704
00:55:41,049 --> 00:55:43,244
and quite enough of this company.

705
00:55:43,318 --> 00:55:45,809
Check me out, Clemens.

706
00:55:45,888 --> 00:55:48,482
l guess that just leaves
the three of us.

707
00:55:48,557 --> 00:55:52,391
Yes, Mr. Shaw.
That just leaves us three.

708
00:55:52,461 --> 00:55:55,225
Mr. Clayton, l think we should
take a break for five minutes.

709
00:55:55,297 --> 00:55:58,061
Tempers seem to be
running a little high.

710
00:55:58,133 --> 00:56:00,727
Ah, come on, Linneman,
l was just startin' to do good.

711
00:56:05,374 --> 00:56:07,808
[ Laughing Continues ]

712
00:56:12,581 --> 00:56:15,778
- Stack me a cooler.
- We'll be in the station
in another hour.

713
00:56:15,851 --> 00:56:18,183
The other guys are the big losers.
You're still okay.

714
00:56:18,253 --> 00:56:21,518
Fix me a deck-- threes and nines.
l'll cut it in on Clayton's deal.

715
00:56:21,590 --> 00:56:23,524
- What do you want Clayton to get ?
- Nothin'.

716
00:56:23,592 --> 00:56:27,756
l want him outta there early. l'm gonna
bust that bastard bookie in one play.

717
00:56:27,829 --> 00:56:31,560
[ Whistle Blowing ]

718
00:56:31,633 --> 00:56:34,602
Four hundred to you, Mr. Jameson.
You're even.

719
00:56:34,670 --> 00:56:36,604
Well, it just wasn't my night.

720
00:56:52,888 --> 00:56:54,822
[ Jameson ]
Oh, l need it.

721
00:56:54,890 --> 00:56:56,949
- You know what time we get in ?
- No, l don't.

722
00:56:58,627 --> 00:57:00,561
Hey, where's your ante ?

723
00:57:08,003 --> 00:57:11,632
[ Lombard ] Every time l had anything,
he stayed in front of me.

724
00:57:34,529 --> 00:57:36,463
Five hundred.

725
00:57:39,167 --> 00:57:41,658
Your five.
One thousand.

726
00:57:43,472 --> 00:57:45,406
l'll fold.

727
00:57:46,942 --> 00:57:48,876
l'll play.

728
00:57:50,545 --> 00:57:52,410
[ Clayton ]
Cards ?

729
00:57:52,481 --> 00:57:54,415
Two.

730
00:57:58,520 --> 00:58:00,317
Three.

731
00:58:28,316 --> 00:58:30,250
Five hundred.

732
00:58:32,387 --> 00:58:36,289
Your five hundred,
and one thousand.

733
00:58:44,266 --> 00:58:47,599
Your one thousand.
l'll raise you two thousand.

734
00:58:51,573 --> 00:58:55,839
Your two thousand.

735
00:58:58,380 --> 00:59:00,575
Mr. Clemens,

736
00:59:00,649 --> 00:59:02,640
give me $10,000 more.

737
00:59:47,963 --> 00:59:50,830
[ Gondorff ]
l'll call.

738
00:59:50,899 --> 00:59:53,663
Four nines.

739
01:00:02,878 --> 01:00:05,506
Four Jacks.

740
01:00:15,457 --> 01:00:17,789
You owe me 15 grand, pal.

741
01:00:31,940 --> 01:00:33,874
Must've left my wallet
in my room.

742
01:00:33,942 --> 01:00:35,933
Don't hand me any of that crap !

743
01:00:36,011 --> 01:00:38,241
When you come to a game like this,
you bring your money !

744
01:00:38,313 --> 01:00:41,009
-How do l know you won't take a powder ?
-No, no, no, no. Now !

745
01:00:41,082 --> 01:00:45,280
l'll tell you what l'll do.
l'll send a boy around
to your room in five minutes.

746
01:00:45,353 --> 01:00:48,845
You better have the money, or it's gonna
be all around Chicago that you welched.

747
01:00:48,924 --> 01:00:51,290
You won't be able
to get a game of jacks !

748
01:00:51,359 --> 01:00:54,328
Cash me in
for the rest of these bums.

749
01:01:06,942 --> 01:01:09,069
[ Sighs ]

750
01:01:09,144 --> 01:01:11,977
You're on, kid.

751
01:01:12,047 --> 01:01:14,641
But l gotta tell you,
it's a hard act to follow.

752
01:01:14,716 --> 01:01:17,617
- How'd it go ?
- We got working money.

753
01:01:17,686 --> 01:01:19,620
- Hey ?
- Yeah ?

754
01:01:19,688 --> 01:01:21,713
- He's steamin'.
- Yeah.

755
01:01:21,790 --> 01:01:23,724
Watch yourself.

756
01:01:30,565 --> 01:01:33,728
[ Floyd ]
Doyle, l know l gave him four threes !

757
01:01:33,802 --> 01:01:35,736
He had to make a switch !

758
01:01:35,804 --> 01:01:37,738
We can't let him
get away with that.

759
01:01:37,806 --> 01:01:41,071
What was l supposed to do ?
Call him for cheating better than me ?

760
01:01:56,191 --> 01:01:58,625
[ Knocks On Door ]

761
01:02:00,328 --> 01:02:02,455
Name's Kelly.
Shaw sent me.

762
01:02:09,938 --> 01:02:12,634
Your boss is quite a card player,
Mr. Kelly.

763
01:02:12,707 --> 01:02:15,870
- How does he do it ?
- He cheats.

764
01:02:18,113 --> 01:02:21,082
Well, in that case, l'll keep my money,
and we'll have another game.

765
01:02:21,149 --> 01:02:23,583
You don't have any to keep.

766
01:02:27,222 --> 01:02:29,918
Here's your wallet.
He hired a dame to take it from you.

767
01:02:31,192 --> 01:02:33,626
Shaw's been plannin'
to beat your game for months.

768
01:02:33,695 --> 01:02:36,163
He's been waiting for you to cheat him
so he could clip you.

769
01:02:36,231 --> 01:02:38,165
[ Grunting ]

770
01:02:38,233 --> 01:02:41,498
Who do you think you're talking to,
errand boy ? Nobody sets me up !

771
01:02:41,569 --> 01:02:43,662
Take him back to the baggage room !
Put one in his ear !

772
01:02:43,738 --> 01:02:46,536
- [ Floyd ] There were four witnesses
at that table !
- Then go back,

773
01:02:46,608 --> 01:02:49,600
get that other goddamn son of a bitch
and dump 'em in the first tunnel we hit.

774
01:02:49,678 --> 01:02:51,908
We're gonna be in the station
in a couple of minutes !

775
01:02:51,980 --> 01:02:54,972
lt ain't gonna look too good
killing a guy you owe money to.

776
01:02:55,050 --> 01:02:59,111
[ Panting ]
There's better ways of takin' him down.

777
01:03:02,857 --> 01:03:05,883
What do you think Shaw would do
if he knew l was tellin' you this ?

778
01:03:09,331 --> 01:03:11,663
Okay.

779
01:03:11,733 --> 01:03:13,667
Why the rat ?

780
01:03:20,442 --> 01:03:23,343
l wanna take over his operation,
and l need you to help me break him.

781
01:03:32,053 --> 01:03:34,715
- Where's my money ?
- Shaw's got it.

782
01:03:34,789 --> 01:03:37,622
How the hell
could l ask him for it back ?

783
01:03:37,692 --> 01:03:40,718
- [ Knocks ]
- We're pullin' in.

784
01:03:46,835 --> 01:03:48,769
l'm givin' you a lift home.

785
01:03:50,638 --> 01:03:53,300
- l was supposed to go with Shaw.
- Explain it to him somehow.

786
01:03:53,375 --> 01:03:56,708
- But he's expecting me.
- l'm givin' you a lift home.

787
01:03:56,778 --> 01:03:58,712
You follow ?

788
01:04:02,150 --> 01:04:05,313
Yeah, sure.
Sure thing.

789
01:04:09,190 --> 01:04:11,624
[ Car Horn Honking ]

790
01:04:17,132 --> 01:04:20,727
- [ Honking Continues ]
- [ Car Doors Closing ]

791
01:04:29,043 --> 01:04:30,977
What makes you think
you can beat him ?

792
01:04:31,045 --> 01:04:32,979
l've been planning this
for two years.

793
01:04:33,047 --> 01:04:35,311
l know his organization
backwards and forwards,

794
01:04:35,383 --> 01:04:38,181
and l need somebody who's respectable
but not completely legit.

795
01:04:38,253 --> 01:04:40,653
l'm a banker, Kelly.
That's legit in this state.

796
01:04:40,722 --> 01:04:44,158
All you gotta do is put down
a bet for me at Shaw's place.
l'll do the rest.

797
01:04:44,225 --> 01:04:47,160
l'll supply the money.
l'll supply the information.

798
01:04:47,228 --> 01:04:50,220
- What about the money
you come to collect ?
- l'll tell him you paid it.

799
01:04:50,298 --> 01:04:52,232
l keep his books.
He trusts me.

800
01:04:52,300 --> 01:04:55,167
lf you help me, l'll pay back the money
he stole out of my own pocket.

801
01:04:55,236 --> 01:04:58,000
- lt's worth that much to you ?
- Yeah.

802
01:04:58,072 --> 01:05:01,269
Oh, yeah.
Maybe a couple of million.

803
01:05:07,916 --> 01:05:11,010
Where do you come from, Kelly ?

804
01:05:11,085 --> 01:05:14,953
From the east side of New York.
A place called Five Points.

805
01:05:15,023 --> 01:05:19,517
- But l got out of there.
- Out and up, huh ?

806
01:05:19,594 --> 01:05:21,858
Hey, Floyd ?

807
01:05:21,930 --> 01:05:25,525
l'm gonna have to keep you away from
this guy. You're liable to get ideas.

808
01:05:43,785 --> 01:05:45,878
l'll be at Klein's Drug Store,

809
01:05:45,954 --> 01:05:49,651
660 South Marshall at 1:30,
if you're interested.

810
01:05:49,724 --> 01:05:53,421
lf l'm not there
by quarter to 2:00, l'm not comin'.

811
01:06:41,442 --> 01:06:43,376
[ Gunshot ]

812
01:07:06,434 --> 01:07:08,527
Hey, Hooker, how'd it go ?

813
01:07:08,603 --> 01:07:10,537
Jake.

814
01:07:12,240 --> 01:07:15,334
- Everything go okay ?
- Yeah, sure. Hell, easy.

815
01:07:25,453 --> 01:07:27,717
- No sign of trouble, huh ?
- No.

816
01:07:27,789 --> 01:07:30,451
- What about Lonnegan ?
- l gave him the breakdown
just like you said.

817
01:07:30,525 --> 01:07:33,016
- And ?
- He's good. He threatened to kill me.

818
01:07:33,094 --> 01:07:37,463
Hell, kid, if they don't do that,
you know you're not gettin' to 'em.

819
01:07:54,849 --> 01:07:57,215
Hello, Doyle.

820
01:07:57,285 --> 01:07:59,549
All right, Riley,
what the hell happened ?

821
01:07:59,621 --> 01:08:01,816
We missed him.

822
01:08:01,889 --> 01:08:04,380
Whoever he is,
he made a fool out of you.

823
01:08:04,459 --> 01:08:06,984
There was no way he could've
known we was in that room.

824
01:08:07,061 --> 01:08:09,325
Somebody must've wised him up.

825
01:08:09,397 --> 01:08:11,627
What does Cole say about that ?

826
01:08:11,699 --> 01:08:13,633
l don't know.
He took it hard.

827
01:08:13,701 --> 01:08:15,760
Get out of here, Riley.

828
01:08:16,838 --> 01:08:18,897
Put Salino onto it.

829
01:08:18,973 --> 01:08:22,773
Salino ? Why waste our best people
on a small-time job ?

830
01:08:22,844 --> 01:08:25,711
This is a nickel-and-dime grifter
we're after, Doyle.

831
01:08:25,780 --> 01:08:27,941
- They'll get him next time.
- They had their chance.

832
01:08:28,016 --> 01:08:30,450
All they did was shoot up
a neighborhood, wake up a few cops.

833
01:08:30,518 --> 01:08:33,954
- Yeah, but--
- l told you to put Salino onto it.

834
01:08:34,022 --> 01:08:37,048
lt may take a little more time,
but there won't be any holes.

835
01:08:37,125 --> 01:08:39,787
Tell Cole l wanna see him
when he comes in.

836
01:08:39,861 --> 01:08:43,456
He won't be comin' in;
not to get bounced off a job anyway.

837
01:08:43,531 --> 01:08:46,125
This is Salino's job, Vince.

838
01:08:46,200 --> 01:08:48,794
Cole wants to muscle in,
that's his business.

839
01:08:48,870 --> 01:08:53,637
But he's breakin' the rules and Salino
won't like it. Now, get me the books.

840
01:09:19,901 --> 01:09:22,665
[ Cash Register Rings ]

841
01:09:26,240 --> 01:09:28,674
[ Men Chattering ]

842
01:09:32,513 --> 01:09:35,949
[ J.J. ]
Those odds on the third race are wrong.

843
01:09:36,017 --> 01:09:38,178
Just a minute.
l'll get 'em.

844
01:09:38,252 --> 01:09:41,779
Don't worry so much.
You're gonna be all right.

845
01:09:41,856 --> 01:09:44,791
Just stay to the back
the first time around.

846
01:09:47,361 --> 01:09:50,296
Put a little of this
on your nose.

847
01:10:33,441 --> 01:10:35,375
[ Lonnegan ]
Kelly ?

848
01:10:39,814 --> 01:10:42,681
You should always look
to the back, kid.

849
01:10:42,750 --> 01:10:45,378
l was afraid you wasn't gonna show.
We haven't got much time.

850
01:10:45,453 --> 01:10:48,251
Get on with it then.

851
01:10:48,322 --> 01:10:50,256
Sometime after 2:00,

852
01:10:50,324 --> 01:10:54,852
a guy's gonna call on that phone
and give you the name of a horse.

853
01:10:54,929 --> 01:10:57,955
All you gotta do is take this
two grand across the street...

854
01:10:58,032 --> 01:11:01,490
to Shaw's place,
and bet it on that pony.

855
01:11:01,569 --> 01:11:05,630
Don't take too much time. We've only got
four minutes after you get the call.

856
01:11:05,706 --> 01:11:08,402
You'll not break him
with a $2,000 bet.

857
01:11:08,476 --> 01:11:10,967
This is just a test.
The big one comes later.

858
01:11:11,045 --> 01:11:13,479
Be careful with that.
That's all l got.

859
01:11:13,548 --> 01:11:16,915
- You were gonna pay me back
out of your own pocket ?
- l am.

860
01:11:16,984 --> 01:11:18,952
After the race.

861
01:11:19,020 --> 01:11:22,478
l gotta get back before Shaw misses me.
Good luck.

862
01:11:45,713 --> 01:11:48,147
[ Quiet Chatter ]

863
01:12:14,442 --> 01:12:16,876
[ Phone Rings ]

864
01:12:18,746 --> 01:12:21,271
[ Twist ]
Yeah ? Go ahead.

865
01:12:21,349 --> 01:12:23,715
[ Woman's Voice On Phone ]
The horse is Blue Note to win.

866
01:12:23,784 --> 01:12:26,309
- Fourth race at Narragansett.
- Got it.

867
01:12:26,387 --> 01:12:28,912
[ Hangs Up Receiver ]

868
01:12:28,990 --> 01:12:31,424
[ Dialing ]

869
01:12:34,395 --> 01:12:36,829
[ Ringing ]

870
01:12:48,009 --> 01:12:49,943
Yeah ?

871
01:12:50,011 --> 01:12:53,503
Blue Note to win in the fourth race
at Narragansett.

872
01:13:29,984 --> 01:13:32,544
[ J.J. On Speakers ] Turning for home,
it's Lady Scout by a length.

873
01:13:32,620 --> 01:13:35,418
Speed Queen a half,
Lady Trust and Miss Petrina.

874
01:13:35,489 --> 01:13:39,482
lnto the stretch, it's Lady Scout ahead,
Speed Queen a half.

875
01:13:39,560 --> 01:13:42,893
- And at the wire,
it's Speed Queen the winner !
- [ Cheering ]

876
01:13:42,964 --> 01:13:45,660
Lady Scout placed
and Miss Petrina showed.

877
01:13:45,733 --> 01:13:48,327
Post numbers
two, five and one.

878
01:13:48,402 --> 01:13:50,336
Taking off at 23.

879
01:13:50,404 --> 01:13:52,338
Look at that.

880
01:13:53,474 --> 01:13:55,408
He's got his apes with him.

881
01:13:57,078 --> 01:14:00,639
Yeah, we're gonna have to
do something about that.

882
01:14:00,715 --> 01:14:05,209
[ J.J. ]
Bubblesome is 10, Beefsteak, 7,

883
01:14:05,286 --> 01:14:08,687
Vote Boy, 6,
Kerry Patch, 12.

884
01:14:08,756 --> 01:14:12,089
Blue Note is 7 to 1.

885
01:14:12,159 --> 01:14:14,889
This is your last call
for the third race at Lincoln Fields.

886
01:14:14,962 --> 01:14:17,055
They're going to the post.

887
01:14:17,131 --> 01:14:20,760
- You may still wager if you hurry.
- There he goes.

888
01:14:23,204 --> 01:14:26,935
At Detroit, the winner,
Speed Queen, paid $7.20,

889
01:14:27,008 --> 01:14:29,067
4.60 and 3.40.

890
01:14:29,143 --> 01:14:31,509
Lady Scout,
$7 and 4.20.

891
01:14:31,579 --> 01:14:33,979
Miss Petrina
paid four dollars.

892
01:14:34,048 --> 01:14:38,951
Last flash at Narragansett.
Lady Higloss, 6 to 5.

893
01:14:41,522 --> 01:14:43,581
l'd think you'd get tired
of losing, Harrigan.

894
01:14:43,657 --> 01:14:46,854
[ Cashier ]
Thank you, Mr. Williams.

895
01:14:46,927 --> 01:14:49,395
Blue Note, $2,000 to win.

896
01:14:49,463 --> 01:14:51,397
Fourth race, Narragansett.

897
01:14:51,465 --> 01:14:53,399
Make sure you see the cash, Eddie.

898
01:14:53,467 --> 01:14:56,527
He's got a name for bettin' money
he doesn't have.

899
01:14:56,604 --> 01:14:58,765
[ J.J. ] We'll give you the results
on that one in a minute.

900
01:14:58,839 --> 01:15:02,502
Ladies and gentlemen,
this is Arnold Rowe,
your caller for the fourth race.

901
01:15:02,576 --> 01:15:06,842
The mile and one-sixteenth handicap
at Narragansett Park, Rhode lsland.

902
01:15:06,914 --> 01:15:10,179
Thirteen thousand dollars
added for three-year-olds and up.

903
01:15:10,251 --> 01:15:14,312
The flag is up,
and they're off and running.

904
01:15:14,388 --> 01:15:17,619
lt's Bubblesome going to the front,
followed by Lady Higloss,

905
01:15:17,691 --> 01:15:21,991
Vote Boy, Chancing,
Beefsteak, Kerry Patch,
and Blue Note trails the field.

906
01:15:22,063 --> 01:15:24,588
Around the clubhouse turn,
it's Bubblesome ahead,

907
01:15:24,665 --> 01:15:26,860
Chancing a half,
Lady Higloss by one,

908
01:15:26,934 --> 01:15:29,869
followed by Vote Boy, Beefsteak,
Kerry Patch and Blue Note.

909
01:15:29,937 --> 01:15:31,996
lnto the second turn,
it's Chancing by a length.

910
01:15:32,073 --> 01:15:34,701
Lady Higloss driving
on the rail and Vote Boy...

911
01:15:34,775 --> 01:15:37,175
followed by Bubblesome, Beefsteak,
Kerry Patch and Blue Note.

912
01:15:37,244 --> 01:15:39,405
- Come on, Chancing !
- Hey, uh--

913
01:15:39,480 --> 01:15:42,347
Lady Higloss a half,
Vote Boy by one.

914
01:15:42,416 --> 01:15:45,908
Lady Higloss is a hell of a finisher.
Chancing's gonna have to open up.

915
01:15:47,922 --> 01:15:50,755
Know anything about a horse
named Blue Note ?

916
01:15:50,825 --> 01:15:54,761
He never done much. Probably in there
just to round out the field.

917
01:15:54,829 --> 01:15:57,889
Chancing's where you
want to have your money.

918
01:16:00,000 --> 01:16:02,992
Great tip you handed me, kid.

919
01:16:03,070 --> 01:16:05,664
- Just give him time.
- [ J.J. ] Chancing by one.

920
01:16:05,739 --> 01:16:08,173
And here comes Blue Note
driving on the outside !

921
01:16:08,242 --> 01:16:10,676
- Nice work, Erie. He loves ya.
- He's third !

922
01:16:10,744 --> 01:16:14,271
Chancing is shortening stride,
and now it's Lady Higloss and Blue Note.

923
01:16:14,348 --> 01:16:16,873
They're head to head.
They're neck and neck.

924
01:16:16,951 --> 01:16:20,011
lt's Lady Higloss, Blue Note;
Lady Higloss, Blue Note.

925
01:16:20,087 --> 01:16:23,352
And Blue Note wins it by a nose !

926
01:16:23,424 --> 01:16:26,518
Lady Higloss is second by three,
and Chancing is third by one.

927
01:16:28,395 --> 01:16:31,558
Who in the blazes is Blue Note ?

928
01:16:31,632 --> 01:16:35,591
The winner, Blue Note,
paid $16, 9.40 and $6.

929
01:16:35,669 --> 01:16:39,696
So you want to have
your money on Chancing, huh ?

930
01:16:39,773 --> 01:16:42,071
[ J.J. ]
Chancing paid 3.80.

931
01:16:42,143 --> 01:16:46,307
Time for the mile and 1/16th:
1:44 and 1.

932
01:16:53,420 --> 01:16:56,753
[ J.J. ]
They're going to the gate at Belmont.

933
01:16:56,824 --> 01:16:58,758
And here are the late odds.

934
01:16:58,826 --> 01:17:01,158
Those garbagemen belong to you ?

935
01:17:01,228 --> 01:17:04,595
Get 'em out of here and don't
bring 'em back. This is a class joint.

936
01:17:04,665 --> 01:17:08,533
- Hey, you, Kelly !
- Yes, sir ?

937
01:17:08,602 --> 01:17:11,571
Run those bums out of here.

938
01:17:11,639 --> 01:17:15,097
- Uh, Mr. Shaw, could l--
- Don't give me any of your lip, kid.

939
01:17:16,443 --> 01:17:18,377
Now, run 'em out of here.

940
01:17:22,082 --> 01:17:24,642
[ Sighs ]
Uh--

941
01:17:24,718 --> 01:17:28,176
[ J.J. ] Time for
the three-quarter mile: 1:11 and 4.

942
01:17:28,255 --> 01:17:33,693
The winner, Panic Relief,
paid 12.40, 8.20 and $5.

943
01:17:33,761 --> 01:17:37,219
Barbara A., 6.20 and 4.

944
01:17:37,298 --> 01:17:40,563
Wilder paid four dollars.

945
01:17:40,634 --> 01:17:43,569
They're at the post
at Belmont at 38.

946
01:17:43,637 --> 01:17:46,697
We're waiting on one.
l'll call Belmont next.

947
01:17:47,908 --> 01:17:50,741
- That's it, fellas !
- [ Laughing ]

948
01:17:51,912 --> 01:17:54,005
[ Laughing Continues ]

949
01:17:54,081 --> 01:17:56,948
- l wanna repeat that--
- All right, J.J.

950
01:17:57,017 --> 01:17:58,951
[ Sighs ]

951
01:18:01,722 --> 01:18:03,656
What do you say, pal ?

952
01:18:09,730 --> 01:18:13,393
[ Rings ]

953
01:18:13,467 --> 01:18:16,766
Yeah ? Mm-hmm.

954
01:18:19,373 --> 01:18:22,206
He's on his way.

955
01:18:35,256 --> 01:18:37,190
Hi, Mutt.

956
01:18:38,058 --> 01:18:41,118
Say, Jeff.

957
01:18:41,195 --> 01:18:43,789
- What'd l tell you ?
- You got lucky once.
That's not enough.

958
01:18:43,864 --> 01:18:46,298
Ah, lucky, hell.
l can do it every time.

959
01:18:46,367 --> 01:18:50,963
- Why don't you then ?
- 'Cause it's better
to do it all at once.

960
01:18:51,038 --> 01:18:53,472
We're gonna put down
400 grand next week.

961
01:18:53,540 --> 01:18:55,974
At five-to-one odds,
that's two million.

962
01:18:56,043 --> 01:18:58,773
- Twenty percent is yours.
- Got a system, Kelly ?

963
01:18:58,846 --> 01:19:02,714
No. You can still lose
with a system.

964
01:19:02,783 --> 01:19:05,308
You're past-posting, aren't you ?

965
01:19:09,523 --> 01:19:11,388
Could be.

966
01:19:11,458 --> 01:19:14,621
- How ?
- You're gonna stay in ?

967
01:19:14,695 --> 01:19:16,890
Not 'til l get some answers.

968
01:19:21,568 --> 01:19:24,093
l got a partner downtown.

969
01:19:24,171 --> 01:19:26,605
He runs the central office
of the Western Union.

970
01:19:26,674 --> 01:19:31,270
Race results from all over
the country come in and go
across his desk to the bookies.

971
01:19:31,345 --> 01:19:35,941
All he does is hold 'em up 'til he can
call us, get a bet down on the winner.

972
01:19:36,016 --> 01:19:38,109
Then he releases the results
to the bookies.

973
01:19:38,185 --> 01:19:41,154
We clean up on a race that's
already been run. You can't miss.

974
01:19:41,221 --> 01:19:43,155
Unless the Western Union dicks
get ahold of it.

975
01:19:52,333 --> 01:19:54,631
You got the 400 grand yet ?

976
01:19:54,702 --> 01:19:57,193
No, not yet, but--

977
01:19:57,271 --> 01:20:01,071
- There's only a grand here.
- Make another bet tomorrow.

978
01:20:01,141 --> 01:20:03,075
Where's my money ?

979
01:20:03,143 --> 01:20:05,373
- l got 16 grand coming.
- You owe me 15 grand already.

980
01:20:05,446 --> 01:20:08,108
lf your setup's as good as you say
it is, there's plenty more to come.

981
01:20:08,182 --> 01:20:09,740
l decide when to place the bets !

982
01:20:09,817 --> 01:20:11,808
Not if you want me
to keep making 'em.

983
01:20:11,885 --> 01:20:14,877
l gotta talk to my partner.
We can't afford to expose too much.

984
01:20:14,955 --> 01:20:16,889
- l'll talk to him myself.
- No !

985
01:20:16,957 --> 01:20:20,654
You've been waiting
a long time for this.
Don't ruin it for yourself.

986
01:20:20,728 --> 01:20:24,789
l'll pick you up tomorrow
at 3:00. You follow ?

987
01:20:58,198 --> 01:21:00,723
Twist, l told him the tale,
but he didn't go for it.

988
01:21:00,801 --> 01:21:02,735
He wants to see my partner
tomorrow at 3:00.

989
01:21:02,803 --> 01:21:04,737
- 3:00 ?
- Yeah.

990
01:21:04,805 --> 01:21:07,740
We'll never get a telegraph
store set up. Any chance
of talking him out of it ?

991
01:21:07,808 --> 01:21:10,333
None. l would've stalled him, but l
didn't have many friends in the room.

992
01:21:10,411 --> 01:21:13,471
Yeah. All right, we'll have to
play him on the fly.

993
01:21:13,547 --> 01:21:15,481
l'll get Eddie looking
for a place.

994
01:21:15,549 --> 01:21:18,518
- Let me know when you got something.
- Sure thing, tootsie.

995
01:21:19,453 --> 01:21:21,387
All right, Hooker !

996
01:21:26,493 --> 01:21:29,155
[ Grunts ]

997
01:21:29,229 --> 01:21:31,163
Stop him !

998
01:21:33,333 --> 01:21:35,267
[ Horn Honks ]

999
01:21:49,883 --> 01:21:52,317
[ Train Passing Overhead ]

1000
01:22:00,661 --> 01:22:03,129
- [ People Grumbling ]
- [ Man ] Hey !

1001
01:22:41,401 --> 01:22:44,393
Hooker ! Hooker !

1002
01:22:44,471 --> 01:22:47,338
l'll get you, you rat !

1003
01:22:47,407 --> 01:22:49,341
Hooker !

1004
01:22:54,581 --> 01:22:57,015
Why didn't you tell me
about Snyder before ?

1005
01:22:57,084 --> 01:22:59,177
- l thought l'd lost him.
- You found him again.

1006
01:22:59,253 --> 01:23:01,881
We're gonna have to
do something about it.

1007
01:23:01,955 --> 01:23:04,924
-What else haven't you been telling me ?
-Nothin'. That's all.

1008
01:23:04,992 --> 01:23:07,017
Hold still.

1009
01:23:07,094 --> 01:23:09,824
Why'd you move out of your room ?

1010
01:23:09,897 --> 01:23:11,831
lt was too noisy.

1011
01:23:11,899 --> 01:23:15,528
You can't play your friends
like marks, Hooker.

1012
01:23:15,602 --> 01:23:18,366
You know how easy it would be
for Lonnegan's guys to get you ?

1013
01:23:18,438 --> 01:23:20,372
All we need
is a couple of days...

1014
01:23:20,440 --> 01:23:23,534
and we can get
the son of a bitch and nail him.

1015
01:23:23,610 --> 01:23:26,135
[ Exhales ]
You just won't learn, will ya ?

1016
01:23:26,213 --> 01:23:29,478
l come in here, teach you stuff
that maybe five guys in the world know;

1017
01:23:29,550 --> 01:23:31,984
stuff most grifters
couldn't do even if they knew it.

1018
01:23:32,052 --> 01:23:35,317
- All you wanna do is run down a bullet.
- l'm askin' a couple of days.

1019
01:23:35,389 --> 01:23:37,653
l can stay clear that long !

1020
01:23:39,560 --> 01:23:42,654
Christ, they'll probably
miss you and hit me.

1021
01:24:18,765 --> 01:24:20,926
- Hey.
- Hi.

1022
01:24:21,001 --> 01:24:24,402
- [ Sneezes ]
- What'll you have ?

1023
01:24:24,471 --> 01:24:26,871
Give me
the, uh, blue plate special.

1024
01:24:26,940 --> 01:24:29,636
One blue plate special.

1025
01:24:41,421 --> 01:24:43,855
[ Cash Register Rings ]

1026
01:24:59,406 --> 01:25:01,340
- You're done ?
- Yeah.

1027
01:25:01,408 --> 01:25:05,845
- Guess l should've had the meat loaf.
- lt isn't any better.

1028
01:25:08,482 --> 01:25:11,007
- Hey, where's June ?
- She quit.

1029
01:25:11,084 --> 01:25:13,348
l'm fillin' in for her
a couple of days...

1030
01:25:13,420 --> 01:25:15,354
until l can get a train
out of here.

1031
01:25:15,422 --> 01:25:17,356
Yeah ?
Where are you going ?

1032
01:25:17,424 --> 01:25:20,655
l don't know.
Depends on what train l get on.

1033
01:25:25,999 --> 01:25:29,264
- Keep it.
- Thanks.

1034
01:25:45,652 --> 01:25:47,586
Let's go.

1035
01:26:09,676 --> 01:26:12,668
Excuse me, ma'am,
but we're looking for Mr., uh--

1036
01:26:12,746 --> 01:26:14,680
- Harmon.
- Uh, Mr. Harmon's office.

1037
01:26:14,748 --> 01:26:18,775
- Mr. Harmon ?
- Yeah. Got a work order
for a painting job.

1038
01:26:18,852 --> 01:26:20,945
- For Mr. Harmon's office ?
- That's right, ma'am.

1039
01:26:21,021 --> 01:26:23,455
Well, hold on.
Just a second.

1040
01:26:28,695 --> 01:26:31,755
[ Knocks On Door,
Door Opens ]

1041
01:26:38,171 --> 01:26:40,264
Hiya.

1042
01:26:40,340 --> 01:26:43,138
- Where to ?
- 110 South Wabash.

1043
01:26:43,210 --> 01:26:46,577
110 South Wabash.
Get going.

1044
01:26:48,482 --> 01:26:50,416
What happened to your face ?

1045
01:26:50,484 --> 01:26:53,214
Ah, got into a fight
with a raggle down on 13th.

1046
01:26:53,286 --> 01:26:55,151
Cut me with her ring.

1047
01:26:55,222 --> 01:26:57,656
You oughta lay off the skirts.

1048
01:26:57,724 --> 01:27:01,751
You don't find any of my boys
messin' around with that kind of trash.

1049
01:27:09,836 --> 01:27:13,897
Brigham signed it, all right. l can't
understand why he didn't tell me.

1050
01:27:13,974 --> 01:27:16,101
Ah, he's like all
them supervisors.

1051
01:27:16,176 --> 01:27:18,269
They think they're
too good for regular people.

1052
01:27:18,345 --> 01:27:21,109
He says he was in here awhile ago
and the place was a mess.

1053
01:27:21,181 --> 01:27:23,479
[ Twist ] We'll hurry
so we don't keep you out too long.

1054
01:27:23,550 --> 01:27:25,484
Why can't l work
with you in here ?

1055
01:27:25,552 --> 01:27:28,612
We gotta cover the floor,
the furniture, everything,
so we don't spill on nothin'.

1056
01:27:28,688 --> 01:27:31,782
lf you want to sit in here with a tarp
over your head, you're welcome to it.

1057
01:27:31,858 --> 01:27:34,622
- How long will you be ?
- An hour or two at the most.

1058
01:27:34,694 --> 01:27:36,628
lt's a small job.

1059
01:28:22,576 --> 01:28:25,010
We'll go in the side door here.

1060
01:28:30,650 --> 01:28:32,584
[ Knocks ]

1061
01:28:36,122 --> 01:28:39,614
Hiya, Les.
Uh, Les, this is Doyle Lonnegan.

1062
01:28:39,693 --> 01:28:42,184
- Mr. Lonnegan, this is Les Harmon.
- How do you do ?

1063
01:28:42,262 --> 01:28:44,321
- Could we, uh--
- What did you bring him here for ?

1064
01:28:44,397 --> 01:28:46,592
l thought it would be a good idea
for him to see the operation.

1065
01:28:46,666 --> 01:28:49,726
l'm having the place painted.
We can't talk in here now.

1066
01:28:49,803 --> 01:28:51,737
Oh.

1067
01:28:51,805 --> 01:28:54,774
We'll have to find someplace else.
Excuse me, Mr. Lonnegan.

1068
01:28:58,912 --> 01:29:02,313
Miss Barnes,
l'm going home a little early.

1069
01:29:02,382 --> 01:29:07,513
lf there are any calls, tell them
they can reach me here tomorrow morning.

1070
01:29:07,587 --> 01:29:09,714
Mr. Lonnegan ?

1071
01:29:41,655 --> 01:29:43,589
l wanna see it one more time.

1072
01:29:43,657 --> 01:29:47,058
l can't do it. We got
telegraph inspectors all over the place.

1073
01:29:47,127 --> 01:29:49,061
One more time isn't gonna
make much difference.

1074
01:29:49,129 --> 01:29:51,927
We got 400 grand
coming in from the coast next week.

1075
01:29:51,998 --> 01:29:54,398
You gonna risk that
on a lousy 15 G's ?

1076
01:29:54,467 --> 01:29:57,630
lf it works again tomorrow,
l'll finance the whole thing.

1077
01:29:57,704 --> 01:30:00,969
Half a million dollars.
Sixty-forty, we split.

1078
01:30:01,041 --> 01:30:04,533
What are you talking-- We've already
got a guy. He's gonna give us half.

1079
01:30:04,611 --> 01:30:08,069
- What am l supposed to say to him ?
- Say to him what you want.

1080
01:30:08,148 --> 01:30:10,582
What l know about your operation,
if l were you,

1081
01:30:10,650 --> 01:30:12,777
l'd be worried
about making me happy.

1082
01:30:12,852 --> 01:30:15,582
Your guy says a week.
How do we know it won't be a month ?

1083
01:30:15,655 --> 01:30:19,022
Lonnegan here's a banker. He can get
the money without any questions asked.

1084
01:30:19,092 --> 01:30:22,027
We can't keep goin' into Shaw's place
and cleanin' up on long shots.

1085
01:30:22,095 --> 01:30:25,496
- He's bound to get wise.
- All right. We'll go for short odds.

1086
01:30:25,565 --> 01:30:27,829
- But it's still--
- You follow ?

1087
01:30:48,455 --> 01:30:50,389
Are you
Lieutenant William Snyder ?

1088
01:30:52,292 --> 01:30:54,522
l don't know.
What's up ?

1089
01:30:54,594 --> 01:30:56,824
F.B.l.

1090
01:30:56,896 --> 01:30:59,831
Special Agent Polk
would like a few words with you.

1091
01:30:59,899 --> 01:31:01,833
You got a couple of minutes ?

1092
01:31:01,901 --> 01:31:03,835
Yeah, sure.

1093
01:31:30,563 --> 01:31:33,464
No, no, no.
lt's got to be south of the river.

1094
01:31:33,533 --> 01:31:38,436
Probably this section in here.
31st, 39th, Morgan and Halstead.

1095
01:31:38,505 --> 01:31:41,440
Now, that's this section here.

1096
01:31:41,508 --> 01:31:46,036
Now, let's break it
into two sections along 35th.

1097
01:31:46,112 --> 01:31:49,445
What the hell is this ?
l got work to do.

1098
01:31:49,516 --> 01:31:51,882
Sit down and shut up, will ya ?

1099
01:31:51,951 --> 01:31:55,944
Try not to live up
to all my expectations.

1100
01:31:56,022 --> 01:32:00,686
Take two men with you.
Work your way south from 31st
to 35th, Morgan and Halstead.

1101
01:32:00,760 --> 01:32:04,196
Go into every place
and let me know what you find.

1102
01:32:10,303 --> 01:32:14,399
We've been told you know
a hustle artist named Johnny Hooker.

1103
01:32:14,474 --> 01:32:17,170
- You know him, or don't you ?
- Yeah, but l don't know where he is.

1104
01:32:17,243 --> 01:32:21,703
Well, we do. He's chumming around
with a big C named Henry Gondorff.

1105
01:32:21,781 --> 01:32:23,715
Ring any bells ?

1106
01:32:23,783 --> 01:32:26,217
Every bunco man in the country
knows Gondorff.

1107
01:32:26,286 --> 01:32:30,416
Well, there's word he's gonna run a con
on the South Side here.

1108
01:32:30,490 --> 01:32:33,687
We've got a year-old Florida warrant
on him, but it's a thin beef.

1109
01:32:33,760 --> 01:32:37,594
He can beat it in court
unless we catch him cold.

1110
01:32:37,664 --> 01:32:40,428
All we want you to do
is pick up Hooker for us.

1111
01:32:40,500 --> 01:32:43,094
Why don't you
pick him up yourself ?

1112
01:32:43,169 --> 01:32:46,798
lf word gets out the feds are in on it,
Gondorff will fold up the whole thing.

1113
01:32:46,873 --> 01:32:49,364
Wouldn't that be too bad.

1114
01:32:49,442 --> 01:32:53,811
Then you'd have to move
out of this nice office you've got here.

1115
01:32:55,115 --> 01:32:57,845
Don't crack wise with me, flatfoot.

1116
01:32:57,917 --> 01:33:01,284
l spent too much time in dumps like this
eating Gondorff's dust...

1117
01:33:01,354 --> 01:33:04,949
while you guys in the bunco squads
get rich tipping him off !

1118
01:33:05,024 --> 01:33:07,686
That's not gonna happen
this time.

1119
01:33:07,760 --> 01:33:10,729
We're not gonna tell
the police we're here.

1120
01:33:10,797 --> 01:33:14,631
You keep your mouth shut and do a job,
there'll be reward bucks in it for you.

1121
01:33:14,701 --> 01:33:19,070
And you better take it, 'cause l
can make you work for us without it.

1122
01:33:19,139 --> 01:33:21,835
What the hell good
is Hooker to you ?

1123
01:33:21,908 --> 01:33:24,638
He's gonna set up Gondorff for us.

1124
01:33:26,446 --> 01:33:29,006
- He'll never do it.
- l think he will.

1125
01:33:49,502 --> 01:33:52,164
[ Buzzing ]

1126
01:33:52,238 --> 01:33:54,672
He's there.
Let's get on it.

1127
01:33:56,242 --> 01:33:58,176
What's the line on Exponent ?

1128
01:33:58,244 --> 01:34:00,872
Uh... 5 to 1. Aah.

1129
01:34:02,115 --> 01:34:04,208
- How's it going ?
- Ah, nothing yet.

1130
01:34:04,284 --> 01:34:07,378
l had a good one on the lead
at Lincoln Fields, but he faded.

1131
01:34:07,453 --> 01:34:12,550
Best we had the last hour
was Love Potion at Rockingham,
and she was 5 to 1.

1132
01:34:12,625 --> 01:34:15,890
All the long shots
coming in today.

1133
01:34:15,962 --> 01:34:17,953
Take 4 to 1 if you have to.

1134
01:34:18,031 --> 01:34:19,965
Okay.

1135
01:34:20,033 --> 01:34:22,831
[ Henry ]
You can forget the boodle, Eddie.

1136
01:34:22,902 --> 01:34:26,702
He could hit us for 15 grand at 4 to 1.
We can't handle that.

1137
01:34:26,773 --> 01:34:28,707
- Give him the shutout.
- Okay.

1138
01:34:28,775 --> 01:34:32,233
Okay, Billie, here we go.

1139
01:34:32,312 --> 01:34:35,475
At the wire, it's Wrecking Crew,
the winner by five.

1140
01:34:35,548 --> 01:34:39,075
Black Mischief, second;
Whichaway, third.

1141
01:34:39,152 --> 01:34:43,179
Wrecking Crew was... 3 to 1.
That's our boy.

1142
01:34:43,256 --> 01:34:45,121
Yeah.

1143
01:34:46,793 --> 01:34:48,727
Henry ?

1144
01:34:52,232 --> 01:34:55,133
Here we go, Henry. We got
a 3 to 1 at Belmont-- Wrecking Crew.

1145
01:34:55,201 --> 01:34:58,637
[ Phone Ringing ]

1146
01:34:58,705 --> 01:35:00,639
Yeah ?

1147
01:35:04,611 --> 01:35:07,205
All right. Okay.

1148
01:35:12,151 --> 01:35:16,247
[ Phone Rings ]

1149
01:35:20,693 --> 01:35:23,719
- Yeah ?
- ln the sixth race at Belmont.

1150
01:35:23,796 --> 01:35:26,560
Wrecking Crew to win;
Black Mischief to place;

1151
01:35:26,633 --> 01:35:28,567
Whichaway to show.

1152
01:35:39,012 --> 01:35:40,946
Wait here.

1153
01:35:45,118 --> 01:35:47,552
[ J.J. ] The winner,
Time To Go, paid seven dollars,

1154
01:35:47,620 --> 01:35:50,111
5.40 and 3.80.

1155
01:35:50,189 --> 01:35:53,647
Joy Flag, $6 and 4.20.

1156
01:35:53,726 --> 01:35:56,661
- Readily paid 3.80 to show.
- [ Phone Ringing ]

1157
01:35:56,729 --> 01:36:00,529
The weather's threatening, but the track
is fast there in Salem, New Hampshire.

1158
01:36:00,600 --> 01:36:03,433
[ Ringing Continues ]

1159
01:36:03,503 --> 01:36:06,563
Here's a late jockey change
there in the fifth at Rockingham.

1160
01:36:06,639 --> 01:36:09,472
R.C. Stark will ride
ltsie-Bitsie.

1161
01:36:09,542 --> 01:36:11,476
- Thank you, sir.
- That's R.C. Stark.

1162
01:36:11,544 --> 01:36:13,978
Five thousand on Black Mischief,
across the board.

1163
01:36:14,047 --> 01:36:15,981
Sixth at Belmont.

1164
01:36:17,417 --> 01:36:20,580
Would you hurry up there, please ?

1165
01:36:20,653 --> 01:36:24,384
[ J.J. ] Wrecking Crew is 3 to 1;
Vale Of Tears, four;

1166
01:36:24,457 --> 01:36:27,187
Black Mischief, five;
Whichaway, six;

1167
01:36:27,260 --> 01:36:31,094
Chief Yeoman, 12;
Peerless Pal is 20;

1168
01:36:31,164 --> 01:36:33,928
and Mariato is, uh, 40.

1169
01:36:34,000 --> 01:36:36,332
And here we go
for the sixth at Belmont.

1170
01:36:36,402 --> 01:36:38,666
lt's five and a half furlongs.
They're at the post.

1171
01:36:38,738 --> 01:36:40,672
- Now.
- The flag is up.

1172
01:36:40,740 --> 01:36:42,674
- And they're off !
- Sixth race, Belmont, 15,000.

1173
01:36:42,742 --> 01:36:45,176
Excuse me, sir. We can't take
any bets once the race is started.

1174
01:36:45,244 --> 01:36:48,407
You can bet on another race
if you care to.

1175
01:36:48,481 --> 01:36:50,847
[ J.J. ] Going into the backstretch,
it's Wrecking Crew by two.

1176
01:36:50,917 --> 01:36:55,115
Whichaway a half, Black Mischief and
Vale Of Tears driving on the outside.

1177
01:36:55,188 --> 01:36:57,884
- Nothin', thank you.
- What happened ?

1178
01:36:57,957 --> 01:37:00,289
l didn't get the bet
down in time.

1179
01:37:00,360 --> 01:37:02,294
Jesus !

1180
01:37:04,564 --> 01:37:07,931
[ J.J. ] Heading for home,
it's Wrecking Crew all alone
by six lengths,

1181
01:37:08,000 --> 01:37:10,093
Whichaway a length,
and Vale of Tears.

1182
01:37:10,169 --> 01:37:12,467
lt's Wrecking Crew,
Whichaway and Black Mischief.

1183
01:37:12,538 --> 01:37:16,338
And at the wire, Wrecking Crew
wins it by six lengths.

1184
01:37:16,409 --> 01:37:20,436
Black Mischief is second
by a head, Whichaway is third,
followed by Vale Of Tears.

1185
01:37:22,448 --> 01:37:25,508
You should've had your money
on Wrecking Crew.

1186
01:37:25,585 --> 01:37:27,985
[ J.J. ] lt's raining and the track
is sloppy at Riverside Park.

1187
01:37:28,054 --> 01:37:33,583
There's a late scratch there.
Transmutate is scratched
in the fifth at Riverside.

1188
01:37:33,659 --> 01:37:36,127
At Belmont,
the winner, Wrecking Crew,

1189
01:37:36,195 --> 01:37:39,528
paid $6, 4.20 and 2.80.

1190
01:37:39,599 --> 01:37:42,500
Black Mischief,
4.60 and 3.20.

1191
01:37:46,873 --> 01:37:49,899
l'll have half a million
here by post time tomorrow.

1192
01:37:49,976 --> 01:37:52,570
Lay it on the first race
where the odds are 4 to 1 or better.

1193
01:37:52,645 --> 01:37:55,671
- Make sure l get
to the window this time.
- How am l gonna do that ?

1194
01:37:55,748 --> 01:37:58,239
l don't know.
Figure it out for yourself, Kelly.

1195
01:38:25,044 --> 01:38:27,604
- [ Clears Throat ]
- Finished ?

1196
01:38:27,680 --> 01:38:31,616
Yeah. Meat loaf, apple pie
and a cup of coffee.

1197
01:38:37,890 --> 01:38:40,688
- Say, what time you get off work here ?
- 2:00 a.m.

1198
01:38:40,760 --> 01:38:45,220
- Yeah ? Doing anything tonight ?
- Yeah. Sleepin'.

1199
01:38:45,298 --> 01:38:47,232
Eighty-five.

1200
01:38:55,208 --> 01:38:57,506
[ Rings ]

1201
01:39:05,084 --> 01:39:08,815
- You got a back door to this place ?
- What's wrong with the front ?

1202
01:39:08,888 --> 01:39:11,652
There's a guy out there
l don't need to see. Don't look around.

1203
01:39:11,724 --> 01:39:14,750
- What does he want ?
- He'd like to kill me.

1204
01:39:14,827 --> 01:39:18,661
Do me a favor. Go into the bathroom,
open the window and wait there.

1205
01:39:18,731 --> 01:39:21,529
- Why should l--
- Do what l tell you,
and everything will be jake.

1206
01:39:21,601 --> 01:39:23,535
Please.

1207
01:39:30,176 --> 01:39:32,110
Thanks.
Good night.

1208
01:40:05,578 --> 01:40:07,512
[ Woman ]
lt's taken.

1209
01:40:25,431 --> 01:40:27,991
Thanks. See ya.

1210
01:40:31,871 --> 01:40:33,270
Shit.

1211
01:41:16,415 --> 01:41:19,350
Salino.
Hey, l wasn't--

1212
01:41:43,242 --> 01:41:46,370
Hey ! Gotcha, Hooker !

1213
01:41:46,445 --> 01:41:48,879
Hey there, Snyder.
Long time no see.

1214
01:41:48,948 --> 01:41:50,882
Get goin' !

1215
01:42:17,576 --> 01:42:19,510
Chuck,

1216
01:42:19,578 --> 01:42:22,570
get this off
to the department right away.

1217
01:42:22,648 --> 01:42:24,582
Yes, sir.

1218
01:42:40,433 --> 01:42:44,164
Hello, Hooker.
Take them off.

1219
01:42:44,236 --> 01:42:46,568
Special Agent Polk, F.B.l.

1220
01:42:46,639 --> 01:42:48,573
- [ Sighs ]
- Have a chair.

1221
01:42:51,844 --> 01:42:54,142
- You want a drink or something ?
- No.

1222
01:42:55,715 --> 01:42:59,344
We want to talk to you
about Henry Gondorff.

1223
01:42:59,418 --> 01:43:01,716
Yeah ?
l don't think l know him.

1224
01:43:01,787 --> 01:43:05,279
Give yourself a couple of seconds.
You wouldn't want to lie to me.

1225
01:43:05,357 --> 01:43:08,622
Lt. Snyder here says you've done
a lot of confidence work in his town.

1226
01:43:08,694 --> 01:43:10,662
Oh, yeah ?
Lt. Snyder doesn't know shit.

1227
01:43:12,431 --> 01:43:15,491
- You ain't got nothin' on me.
- Yeah ?

1228
01:43:15,568 --> 01:43:17,502
How 'bout counterfeiting ?

1229
01:43:21,507 --> 01:43:25,910
We've got a tip that Gondorff is gonna
run a con on the South Side here.

1230
01:43:25,978 --> 01:43:29,243
All you've gotta do is tell us
when he's gonna play his chump.

1231
01:43:29,315 --> 01:43:32,182
We come in at the sting,
make the pinch, and...

1232
01:43:32,251 --> 01:43:35,414
you walk out
free as a bird.

1233
01:43:35,488 --> 01:43:37,922
No.

1234
01:43:37,990 --> 01:43:41,585
You wanna spend the next 20 years
in a federal penitentiary...

1235
01:43:41,660 --> 01:43:43,093
starting tonight ?

1236
01:43:43,162 --> 01:43:44,595
l'll make parole.

1237
01:43:45,765 --> 01:43:48,529
Like hell.
You won't even get a review.

1238
01:43:48,601 --> 01:43:50,535
l'll chance it.

1239
01:43:53,372 --> 01:43:57,308
Okay. lf that's
the way you want it.

1240
01:43:57,376 --> 01:44:00,777
We might even provide you with a little
company on your way up the river.

1241
01:44:00,846 --> 01:44:03,314
That wife of Luther Coleman's--
what was her name ?

1242
01:44:03,382 --> 01:44:06,010
- Alva.
- Alva.

1243
01:44:06,085 --> 01:44:08,883
That's it.
Alva Coleman.

1244
01:44:08,954 --> 01:44:11,514
Pretty fair grifter
in her time.

1245
01:44:11,590 --> 01:44:14,150
Snyder's given us
quite a folder on her.

1246
01:44:14,226 --> 01:44:17,855
Nothing major by itself,
but, uh,

1247
01:44:17,930 --> 01:44:21,229
put 'em all together,
it could add up to a lot of years.

1248
01:44:22,701 --> 01:44:26,797
- You stink, mister.
- Don't be a sap.

1249
01:44:26,872 --> 01:44:28,965
lt's not her l want.

1250
01:44:29,041 --> 01:44:31,805
lf you're too dumb
to save yourself,

1251
01:44:31,877 --> 01:44:34,311
there's no sense
dragging her down with ya.

1252
01:44:56,468 --> 01:44:58,402
lt's over, Hooker.

1253
01:45:00,105 --> 01:45:03,040
You can save me
a lot of trouble.

1254
01:45:03,108 --> 01:45:07,545
But l'm gonna get Henry Gondorff
whether you help me out or not.

1255
01:45:22,061 --> 01:45:25,053
- Will you wait
'til the chump is played ?
- Hell, yes.

1256
01:45:25,130 --> 01:45:27,564
We don't care about the mark.
He deserves what he gets.

1257
01:45:27,633 --> 01:45:31,569
l mean completely played. You come in
before we beat him, and l'll kill him.

1258
01:45:32,705 --> 01:45:34,798
All right, Hooker.

1259
01:45:34,874 --> 01:45:38,537
But you try to take it on the lam,
and we'll shoot you down on sight.

1260
01:45:46,719 --> 01:45:49,279
As long as l get
to finish the play.

1261
01:45:56,829 --> 01:45:59,263
[ Sighs ]

1262
01:45:59,331 --> 01:46:01,993
What is it, kid ?
You're not saying much.

1263
01:46:02,067 --> 01:46:05,264
- Just got the jumps.
- [ Knocking ]
- Come in.

1264
01:46:05,337 --> 01:46:09,103
Things are a little slow.
l wanna open the round for the girls.

1265
01:46:09,174 --> 01:46:11,108
Sure.

1266
01:46:14,847 --> 01:46:17,111
Take it easy, kid.
We're not gonna lose him now.

1267
01:46:17,182 --> 01:46:20,447
We had him ten years ago
when he decided to be somebody.

1268
01:46:20,519 --> 01:46:23,716
Believe me, l've seen
enough to know. Ten.

1269
01:46:23,789 --> 01:46:25,723
- Twenty.
- Thirty.

1270
01:46:25,791 --> 01:46:28,225
- Go.
- Thirty-one.

1271
01:46:32,298 --> 01:46:34,459
Aagh.

1272
01:46:34,533 --> 01:46:37,593
How many guys you conned
in your life, Henry ?

1273
01:46:37,670 --> 01:46:40,468
l don't know.
Two, three hundred.

1274
01:46:40,539 --> 01:46:44,942
Sometimes we played two a day
when l was with O'Shea's mob.

1275
01:46:45,010 --> 01:46:47,740
Of course,
Chicago was a rigged town.

1276
01:46:47,813 --> 01:46:52,375
The fix was in; the dicks
took their end without a beef.

1277
01:46:52,451 --> 01:46:56,353
We had it down to a business.
[ Chuckles ]

1278
01:46:56,422 --> 01:46:58,913
And it really stunk, kid.

1279
01:46:58,991 --> 01:47:03,325
No sense in bein' a grifter if it's
the same thing as bein' a citizen.

1280
01:47:03,395 --> 01:47:07,331
l got packin' to do. l'm gonna be
a hot number again after tomorrow.

1281
01:47:11,503 --> 01:47:14,438
.. [ Calliope ]

1282
01:47:18,577 --> 01:47:22,570
l wouldn't ask you to do this, you know,
if it weren't for Luther.

1283
01:47:22,648 --> 01:47:26,709
Nothin's gonna make up for Luther.
Revenge is for suckers.

1284
01:47:26,785 --> 01:47:29,447
l've been griftin' 30 years.
l never got any.

1285
01:47:31,924 --> 01:47:33,858
Then why're you doin' it ?

1286
01:47:35,327 --> 01:47:38,194
lt seems worthwhile,
doesn't it ?

1287
01:47:43,802 --> 01:47:45,736
See ya.

1288
01:47:50,476 --> 01:47:54,242
- .. [ Calliope Continues ]
- [ Women Shouting ]

1289
01:49:34,346 --> 01:49:36,780
[ Door Closes ]

1290
01:50:06,245 --> 01:50:08,145
Looks like he missed you.

1291
01:50:08,213 --> 01:50:12,081
Yeah, yeah.
This time, anyway.

1292
01:50:12,151 --> 01:50:14,244
Good night, Mrs. Hillard.

1293
01:50:21,326 --> 01:50:24,818
l was wonderin' if you might
want to come out for a while,

1294
01:50:24,897 --> 01:50:26,831
maybe have a drink
or something.

1295
01:50:26,899 --> 01:50:30,426
You move right along, don't you ?

1296
01:50:30,502 --> 01:50:33,027
Hey, l don't mean nothin' by it.

1297
01:50:33,105 --> 01:50:36,097
l just don't know many
regular girls, is all.

1298
01:50:36,175 --> 01:50:38,541
And you expect me
to come out just like that ?

1299
01:50:38,610 --> 01:50:42,171
lf l expected somethin', l wouldn't
still be standin' here in the hall.

1300
01:50:42,247 --> 01:50:45,114
l don't even know you.

1301
01:50:45,184 --> 01:50:49,553
You know me.
l'm just like you.

1302
01:50:49,621 --> 01:50:53,022
lt's 2:00 in the morning,
and l don't know nobody.

1303
01:51:18,951 --> 01:51:22,250
Come on, Henry.
Knock off.

1304
01:51:22,321 --> 01:51:25,757
- You've done everything you can.
- Hmm.

1305
01:52:30,722 --> 01:52:32,656
[ Horn Honking ]

1306
01:52:47,239 --> 01:52:49,673
[ Train Rumbling ]

1307
01:54:07,719 --> 01:54:10,517
[ Door Closes ]

1308
01:54:43,021 --> 01:54:45,455
[ Cash Register Rings ]

1309
01:55:51,490 --> 01:55:54,857
[ Rings ]

1310
01:55:55,927 --> 01:55:59,021
- Yeah ? Polk.
- Polk, this is Hooker.

1311
01:55:59,097 --> 01:56:01,691
- Ready ?
- Yeah, go ahead.

1312
01:56:01,766 --> 01:56:03,927
Everything's all set.
There'll be a guy or two at the door.

1313
01:56:04,002 --> 01:56:06,197
Nobody's carrying any heaters,
so you shouldn't have any trouble.

1314
01:56:06,271 --> 01:56:08,205
Okay. See you there.

1315
01:57:11,002 --> 01:57:14,938
She was gonna kill you, kid.
Her name's Loretta Salino.

1316
01:57:15,006 --> 01:57:18,601
Lonnegan's people set her up
in the diner. Come on.

1317
01:57:18,677 --> 01:57:21,168
Let's get out of here.

1318
01:57:21,246 --> 01:57:23,180
Come on !

1319
01:57:27,886 --> 01:57:29,820
Come on !

1320
01:57:35,093 --> 01:57:37,789
She could have killed me last night.

1321
01:57:37,862 --> 01:57:40,456
Too many people could have
seen you go in her room.

1322
01:57:40,532 --> 01:57:45,231
She was a real professional.
Used to work in the Dutch Schultz mob.

1323
01:57:45,303 --> 01:57:47,897
Who are you ?

1324
01:57:47,973 --> 01:57:50,407
Gondorff asked me
to look after you.

1325
01:58:00,485 --> 01:58:03,921
Snyder, we just got a tip
that Gondorff's mark...

1326
01:58:03,989 --> 01:58:06,082
is some big New York wheel.

1327
01:58:06,157 --> 01:58:08,785
As soon as we're inside,
you get him out of there fast...

1328
01:58:08,860 --> 01:58:10,794
before the reporters show up.

1329
01:58:10,862 --> 01:58:13,626
l don't want any big shots around
to mess this up for me.

1330
01:58:13,698 --> 01:58:15,632
All right, let's go !

1331
01:58:31,916 --> 01:58:34,350
[ Engine Starts ]

1332
01:58:36,154 --> 01:58:39,123
[ Door Opens ]

1333
01:59:14,259 --> 01:59:16,386
[ Buzzing ]

1334
01:59:16,461 --> 01:59:19,259
Let's go, guys !

1335
01:59:19,330 --> 01:59:21,264
The flag is up, kid.

1336
01:59:27,772 --> 01:59:30,605
- Anytime, J.J.
- l'm workin' on it.

1337
01:59:41,686 --> 01:59:44,018
We got one, Billie.
Here we go.

1338
01:59:47,792 --> 01:59:51,228
[ Phone Ringing ]

1339
01:59:58,136 --> 02:00:00,900
- Yeah ?
- Place it on Lucky Dan,

1340
02:00:00,972 --> 02:00:03,406
third race at Riverside Park.

1341
02:00:23,161 --> 02:00:25,755
[ J.J. ]
1:11 and 3/5ths seconds.

1342
02:00:25,830 --> 02:00:28,856
They were off at 21.

1343
02:00:28,933 --> 02:00:33,131
Last call on the third
at Riverside Park.

1344
02:00:33,204 --> 02:00:35,138
They're at the post.

1345
02:00:35,206 --> 02:00:37,936
At Havre De Grace,
the winner, Light Chatter,

1346
02:00:38,009 --> 02:00:41,536
paid, uh, 5.40, 3.80...

1347
02:00:41,613 --> 02:00:43,547
and 2.40.

1348
02:00:43,615 --> 02:00:47,779
- Blacksod--
- $500,000 to win.

1349
02:00:47,852 --> 02:00:50,377
Lucky Dan,
third race at Riverside.

1350
02:00:52,457 --> 02:00:54,721
- [ J.J.] Post time
for the third race...
- You heard me.

1351
02:00:54,793 --> 02:00:57,887
- is 2:27.
- Hold on, sir.

1352
02:00:57,962 --> 02:00:59,896
- There's a jockey change...
- l'll get the manager.

1353
02:00:59,964 --> 02:01:01,898
in the fourth at Belmont.

1354
02:01:01,966 --> 02:01:06,232
Jay Stout will ride Flying Cross.

1355
02:01:06,304 --> 02:01:11,298
See that guy over there ? He just bet
a half million dollars on Lucky Dan.

1356
02:01:11,376 --> 02:01:14,072
[ J.J. ]
The winner at Rockingham Park,

1357
02:01:14,145 --> 02:01:17,080
Enfin, paid 6.10,

1358
02:01:17,148 --> 02:01:19,912
4.30 and 2.50.

1359
02:01:24,022 --> 02:01:25,956
What's your problem ?

1360
02:01:26,024 --> 02:01:30,358
l'm putting half a million
dollars on Lucky Dan to win,
third race at Riverside.

1361
02:01:30,428 --> 02:01:34,330
Can't lay that off in time.
A bet like that could break us.

1362
02:01:36,367 --> 02:01:39,427
Not only are you a cheat,

1363
02:01:39,504 --> 02:01:41,529
you're a gutless cheat as well.

1364
02:01:46,277 --> 02:01:49,371
- What are the odds ?
- Four to one.

1365
02:01:52,517 --> 02:01:54,451
Take all of it.

1366
02:01:54,519 --> 02:01:57,454
[ People Murmuring ]

1367
02:02:05,396 --> 02:02:09,833
Ladies and gentlemen,
this is Arnold Rowe calling
the third race at Riverside.

1368
02:02:09,901 --> 02:02:13,268
This is a claiming race
for $1,500 for three-year-olds and up.

1369
02:02:13,338 --> 02:02:15,431
lt's been raining,
and the track is muddy.

1370
02:02:15,506 --> 02:02:19,533
The flag is up,
and they're off and running.

1371
02:02:19,611 --> 02:02:21,806
Dr. Twink is going to the front,

1372
02:02:21,880 --> 02:02:24,906
followed by Lucky Dan,
lma Dreamer, Orkin,

1373
02:02:24,983 --> 02:02:28,180
Josie G., Chi Chi
and Little Star.

1374
02:02:28,253 --> 02:02:31,188
Around the clubhouse turn,
it's Lucky Dan ahead,

1375
02:02:31,256 --> 02:02:33,588
- Dr. Twink a length, Orkin a half,
- [ Shouting ]

1376
02:02:33,658 --> 02:02:37,992
followed by lma Dreamer,
Josie G., Chi Chi and Little Star.

1377
02:02:38,062 --> 02:02:39,996
lnto the backstretch,

1378
02:02:40,064 --> 02:02:42,658
it's Lucky Dan a length,
Dr. Twink a half,

1379
02:02:42,734 --> 02:02:45,294
Orkin a head,
lma Dreamer by one.

1380
02:02:45,370 --> 02:02:47,998
Sorry, l couldn't wait.
Everything going all right ?

1381
02:02:48,072 --> 02:02:51,041
You got nothing
to worry about.

1382
02:02:51,109 --> 02:02:55,136
- Dr. Twink a length, Orkin a half.
- l put it all on Lucky Dan.

1383
02:02:55,213 --> 02:02:57,807
Half a million dollars to win.

1384
02:02:57,882 --> 02:03:00,851
- lnto the far turn,
Lucky Dan still a length.
- To win ?

1385
02:03:00,919 --> 02:03:04,719
l said place !
Place it on Lucky--

1386
02:03:04,789 --> 02:03:07,189
That horse is gonna run second !

1387
02:03:07,258 --> 02:03:11,695
lma Dreamer a half, Dr. Twink a half and
Orkin by two, followed by Little Star.

1388
02:03:11,763 --> 02:03:13,731
lt's a driving finish !

1389
02:03:13,798 --> 02:03:16,426
- There's been a mistake.
Give me my money back !
- No, l'm sorry--

1390
02:03:16,501 --> 02:03:19,231
l tell you there's been a mistake !
Give me my goddamn money back !

1391
02:03:20,705 --> 02:03:23,230
All right, everybody. F.B.l. !
Don't anybody try to leave.

1392
02:03:23,308 --> 02:03:27,267
Stand on your feet, put your hands
over your head and move nice and slow.

1393
02:03:27,345 --> 02:03:30,508
Snyder !

1394
02:03:30,581 --> 02:03:34,608
Get 'em up against the wall.
Make sure they're not carrying anything.

1395
02:03:37,422 --> 02:03:40,289
Hello, Henry.
lt's been a long time.

1396
02:03:40,358 --> 02:03:42,758
But it's over.

1397
02:03:42,827 --> 02:03:45,057
Okay, kid, you can go.

1398
02:03:47,231 --> 02:03:50,257
[ Polk ] All right,
l said hands up. Keep 'em up !

1399
02:03:50,335 --> 02:03:53,896
Come on. Move 'em back !
Put 'em up !

1400
02:03:55,473 --> 02:03:57,304
[ People Screaming ]

1401
02:03:57,375 --> 02:04:01,072
[ Screaming Continues ]

1402
02:04:13,257 --> 02:04:16,158
Get him out.
Get him out !

1403
02:04:17,228 --> 02:04:20,163
Come on !
Gotta get you out of here !

1404
02:04:30,141 --> 02:04:32,575
- Come on !
- But my money's in there !

1405
02:04:32,643 --> 02:04:35,407
There's a couple
of dead guys in there too.
You can't get mixed up in that.

1406
02:04:35,480 --> 02:04:38,347
You don't understand. There's
a half a million dollars in there !

1407
02:04:48,259 --> 02:04:50,193
He's gone.

1408
02:04:56,968 --> 02:04:59,027
Okay, Henry, all clear.

1409
02:05:01,572 --> 02:05:05,474
[ Laughter ]

1410
02:05:17,955 --> 02:05:20,651
Can you believe it ?
We pulled it off.

1411
02:05:20,725 --> 02:05:24,684
lt's a nice con, Hickey. l thought you
were the feds myself when you came in.

1412
02:05:24,762 --> 02:05:28,061
No trouble, Henry.
Snyder went for it all the way.

1413
02:05:28,132 --> 02:05:31,863
You should've seen the rag
he lit under Lonnegan !

1414
02:05:36,808 --> 02:05:39,242
Well, kid, you beat him.

1415
02:05:40,545 --> 02:05:43,309
You're right, Henry.
lt's not enough.

1416
02:05:45,983 --> 02:05:47,917
But it's close.

1417
02:05:51,222 --> 02:05:54,248
Okay, guys,
let's take this place apart fast.

1418
02:05:54,325 --> 02:05:57,624
You can pick up your splits from Eddie
at Boudreau's tonight.

1419
02:06:02,333 --> 02:06:04,267
Nice goin', J.J.

1420
02:06:07,205 --> 02:06:10,265
Ohh, Henry !

1421
02:06:16,180 --> 02:06:18,307
[ Man ] Comin' through.
Comin' through.

1422
02:06:25,690 --> 02:06:28,124
You're not gonna stick around
for your share ?

1423
02:06:29,193 --> 02:06:31,627
Nah. l'd only blow it.

1424
02:07:14,338 --> 02:07:16,932
[ Man ] One, two.
One, two, three.

1425
02:07:17,008 --> 02:07:20,444
.. [ Band Playing Ragtime ]

